WEBVTT

00:00:01.397 --> 00:00:03.649 line:90% position:50% align:center
Welcome to JW Broadcasting®

00:00:03.649 --> 00:00:05.985 line:90% position:50% align:center
for January 2024!

00:00:25.004 --> 00:00:26.463 line:10% position:50% align:center
In November,

00:00:26.463 --> 00:00:28.591 line:10% position:50% align:center
we enjoyed the exciting first half

00:00:28.591 --> 00:00:30.801 line:10% position:50% align:center
of the annual meeting program.

00:00:30.801 --> 00:00:33.387 line:10% position:50% align:center
Now please enjoy Part 2!

00:00:34.555 --> 00:00:38.100 line:90% position:50% align:center
We’ll now enjoy the first of two symposiums.

00:00:38.100 --> 00:00:41.395 line:90% position:50% align:center
Each speaker will introduce the next.

00:00:41.395 --> 00:00:43.564 line:90% position:50% align:center
So let’s give our attention, please,

00:00:43.564 --> 00:00:45.983 line:90% position:50% align:center
to Brother Jeffrey Winder,

00:00:45.983 --> 00:00:48.360 line:90% position:50% align:center
who will consider the theme

00:00:48.360 --> 00:00:51.447 line:90% position:50% align:center
“How Does the Light Get Brighter?”

00:00:53.532 --> 00:00:57.536 line:90% position:50% align:center
In recent years,
the annual meeting has been an occasion

00:00:57.536 --> 00:01:01.916 line:90% position:50% align:center
where clarified understanding
of Bible truths, new light,

00:01:01.916 --> 00:01:05.210 line:90% position:50% align:center
has been announced and explained.

00:01:05.210 --> 00:01:08.505 line:90% position:50% align:center
Of course, it’s not at every annual meeting
that this takes place,

00:01:08.505 --> 00:01:10.841 line:90% position:50% align:center
but when Jehovah makes something known,

00:01:10.841 --> 00:01:15.346 line:90% position:50% align:center
often it’s at the annual meeting
where it is announced.

00:01:16.096 --> 00:01:18.641 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, will there be new light today?

00:01:19.683 --> 00:01:21.936 line:90% position:50% align:center
I think Brother Cook
already spilled the beans a bit,

00:01:23.646 --> 00:01:25.773 line:90% position:50% align:center
but we look forward to seeing

00:01:25.773 --> 00:01:30.361 line:90% position:50% align:center
what is in store for our program.

00:01:30.361 --> 00:01:32.905 line:90% position:50% align:center
But have you ever wondered, though,

00:01:32.905 --> 00:01:36.116 line:90% position:50% align:center
‘How exactly does Jehovah reveal

00:01:36.116 --> 00:01:38.369 line:90% position:50% align:center
‘clarified understanding of the Scriptures,

00:01:38.369 --> 00:01:41.413 line:90% position:50% align:center
new light, in modern times?’

00:01:41.413 --> 00:01:44.124 line:90% position:50% align:center
When the Governing Body is meeting together

00:01:44.124 --> 00:01:47.086 line:90% position:50% align:center
as “the faithful and discreet slave,”

00:01:47.086 --> 00:01:49.129 line:90% position:50% align:center
how does it work?

00:01:49.129 --> 00:01:51.632 line:90% position:50% align:center
How exactly does the light get brighter?

00:01:51.632 --> 00:01:54.468 line:90% position:50% align:center
How does Jehovah use that arrangement

00:01:54.468 --> 00:01:57.513 line:90% position:50% align:center
to clarify our understanding?

00:01:58.597 --> 00:02:03.018 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, first of all,
what do we know from the Scriptures?

00:02:03.018 --> 00:02:05.396 line:90% position:50% align:center
Let’s look at four points.

00:02:05.396 --> 00:02:07.398 line:90% position:50% align:center
The first one is this:

00:02:07.398 --> 00:02:12.361 line:90% position:50% align:center
By what means does Jehovah reveal new light?

00:02:12.361 --> 00:02:15.698 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, for that,
we can turn to 1 Corinthians chapter 2

00:02:19.159 --> 00:02:22.204 line:90% position:50% align:center
and read together 1 Corinthians 2:10:

00:02:24.581 --> 00:02:28.002 line:90% position:50% align:center
“For it is to us God has revealed them

00:02:28.002 --> 00:02:30.421 line:90% position:50% align:center
“through his spirit,

00:02:30.421 --> 00:02:33.048 line:90% position:50% align:center
“for the spirit searches into all things,

00:02:33.048 --> 00:02:35.926 line:90% position:50% align:center
even the deep things of God.”

00:02:35.926 --> 00:02:39.304 line:90% position:50% align:center
So clearly—
By what means does Jehovah reveal new light?

00:02:39.304 --> 00:02:40.806 line:90% position:50% align:center
It’s by his spirit.

00:02:40.806 --> 00:02:43.017 line:90% position:50% align:center
We recognize the key role

00:02:43.017 --> 00:02:46.061 line:90% position:50% align:center
that Jehovah’s spirit
has in revealing the truth.

00:02:47.271 --> 00:02:48.689 line:90% position:50% align:center
Point two:

00:02:48.689 --> 00:02:53.444 line:90% position:50% align:center
To whom does Jehovah reveal
clarified understanding?

00:02:53.444 --> 00:02:57.698 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, for that we can turn
to the book of Matthew chapter 24

00:02:59.950 --> 00:03:03.412 line:90% position:50% align:center
and read together Matthew 24:45:

00:03:05.497 --> 00:03:08.834 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Who really is
the faithful and discreet slave

00:03:08.834 --> 00:03:11.545 line:90% position:50% align:center
“whom his master
appointed over his domestics,

00:03:11.545 --> 00:03:15.632 line:90% position:50% align:center
to give them their food at the proper time?”

00:03:15.632 --> 00:03:19.803 line:90% position:50% align:center
So clearly, Christ has appointed
“the faithful and discreet slave,”

00:03:19.803 --> 00:03:23.348 line:90% position:50% align:center
and it is through this channel
that Jehovah, through Christ,

00:03:23.348 --> 00:03:26.477 line:90% position:50% align:center
works to provide spiritual food.

00:03:27.436 --> 00:03:29.730 line:90% position:50% align:center
So just with those first two points,

00:03:29.730 --> 00:03:34.151 line:90% position:50% align:center
it’s very clear to us how spiritual truth,
new understanding,

00:03:34.151 --> 00:03:38.155 line:90% position:50% align:center
is communicated from heaven to earth
by means of the holy spirit

00:03:38.155 --> 00:03:40.532 line:90% position:50% align:center
through the channel
of “the faithful and discreet slave.”

00:03:41.617 --> 00:03:43.619 line:90% position:50% align:center
Question number three:

00:03:43.619 --> 00:03:46.997 line:90% position:50% align:center
When does Jehovah reveal new light?

00:03:47.998 --> 00:03:52.419 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, we just have to look back
to verse 45 of Matthew chapter 24.

00:03:52.419 --> 00:03:56.006 line:90% position:50% align:center
The slave will provide
the “food at the proper time.”

00:03:56.006 --> 00:03:59.968 line:90% position:50% align:center
There’s a clear timing element
indicated there, isn’t there?

00:03:59.968 --> 00:04:04.973 line:90% position:50% align:center
And so Jehovah reveals
clarified understanding at his time

00:04:04.973 --> 00:04:09.061 line:90% position:50% align:center
when it is needed and when it
will help us to carry out his will.

00:04:10.771 --> 00:04:12.189 line:90% position:50% align:center
Number four:

00:04:12.189 --> 00:04:15.901 line:90% position:50% align:center
At what rate does he reveal new light?

00:04:15.901 --> 00:04:17.903 line:90% position:50% align:center
Is it all at once, like a dump truck?

00:04:17.903 --> 00:04:21.448 line:90% position:50% align:center
Or is it metered out, like a trickle?

00:04:21.448 --> 00:04:26.328 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, the answer to that is found
in the book of Proverbs chapter 4

00:04:28.372 --> 00:04:30.207 line:90% position:50% align:center
and verse 18

00:04:32.000 --> 00:04:33.877 line:90% position:50% align:center
—Proverbs 4:18:

00:04:33.877 --> 00:04:37.256 line:90% position:50% align:center
“But the path of the righteous
is like the bright morning light

00:04:37.256 --> 00:04:42.219 line:90% position:50% align:center
that grows brighter and brighter
until full daylight.”

00:04:42.219 --> 00:04:45.597 line:90% position:50% align:center
So the Bible here
uses the illustration of daylight.

00:04:45.597 --> 00:04:47.599 line:90% position:50% align:center
And what does that teach us?

00:04:47.599 --> 00:04:51.353 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, <i>The Watchtower</i>  said:
“These words aptly apply to the way

00:04:51.353 --> 00:04:56.358 line:90% position:50% align:center
in which Jehovah reveals
his purpose to his people—gradually.”

00:04:56.358 --> 00:05:00.028 line:90% position:50% align:center
So just as daylight grows
brighter and brighter gradually,

00:05:00.028 --> 00:05:03.866 line:90% position:50% align:center
a proper understanding
of Bible truths comes gradually

00:05:03.866 --> 00:05:08.871 line:90% position:50% align:center
as we need it and as we are
able to absorb it and use it.

00:05:08.871 --> 00:05:11.373 line:90% position:50% align:center
And we appreciate that, don’t we?

00:05:11.373 --> 00:05:16.170 line:90% position:50% align:center
It’s easier on our eyes when literal light
gets brighter gradually.

00:05:16.170 --> 00:05:20.340 line:90% position:50% align:center
And so it is with the understanding
of Jehovah’s purpose as well.

00:05:20.340 --> 00:05:23.177 line:90% position:50% align:center
For example, think about Abraham.

00:05:23.177 --> 00:05:27.431 line:90% position:50% align:center
Could Abraham have handled
and absorbed a complete understanding

00:05:27.431 --> 00:05:30.058 line:90% position:50% align:center
of Jehovah’s will at his time

00:05:30.058 --> 00:05:32.519 line:90% position:50% align:center
—how he would use the 12 tribes of Israel,

00:05:32.519 --> 00:05:36.899 line:90% position:50% align:center
the Mosaic Law, the understanding of Christ,
the payment of the ransom,

00:05:36.899 --> 00:05:39.860 line:90% position:50% align:center
the first-century Christian congregation,
the heavenly hope,

00:05:39.860 --> 00:05:42.696 line:90% position:50% align:center
the last days,
and details about the great tribulation?

00:05:42.696 --> 00:05:45.157 line:90% position:50% align:center
No way.
He couldn’t handle all of that.

00:05:45.157 --> 00:05:46.992 line:90% position:50% align:center
He didn’t need it.

00:05:46.992 --> 00:05:49.119 line:90% position:50% align:center
But Abraham had what he needed

00:05:49.119 --> 00:05:52.915 line:90% position:50% align:center
to serve Jehovah acceptably
during the time that he lived.

00:05:53.916 --> 00:05:57.294 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, we have the privilege
to live during the last days

00:05:57.294 --> 00:06:01.590 line:90% position:50% align:center
when “true knowledge”
was foretold to “become abundant.”

00:06:01.590 --> 00:06:04.676 line:90% position:50% align:center
But even still, it is released and made known

00:06:04.676 --> 00:06:06.970 line:90% position:50% align:center
at a pace that we can absorb,

00:06:06.970 --> 00:06:09.431 line:90% position:50% align:center
that we can handle, and that we can use.

00:06:09.431 --> 00:06:11.516 line:90% position:50% align:center
And we thank Jehovah for that.

00:06:13.352 --> 00:06:18.023 line:90% position:50% align:center
So this is what we know from the Scriptures
and from our own experience as well

00:06:18.023 --> 00:06:20.943 line:90% position:50% align:center
about how the light
gets brighter in modern times.

00:06:20.943 --> 00:06:23.654 line:90% position:50% align:center
It comes about by means of the holy spirit,

00:06:23.654 --> 00:06:26.698 line:90% position:50% align:center
through his channel
of “the faithful and discreet slave,”

00:06:26.698 --> 00:06:30.953 line:90% position:50% align:center
He reveals it gradually,
and at a time that it is needed.

00:06:32.454 --> 00:06:37.125 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, knowing this, then, we are not
embarrassed about adjustments that are made,

00:06:37.125 --> 00:06:39.628 line:90% position:50% align:center
nor is an apology needed

00:06:39.628 --> 00:06:42.631 line:90% position:50% align:center
for not getting it exactly right previously.

00:06:42.631 --> 00:06:45.133 line:90% position:50% align:center
We understand that this
is how Jehovah operates.

00:06:45.133 --> 00:06:48.887 line:90% position:50% align:center
He reveals matters gradually
when it is needed.

00:06:49.805 --> 00:06:54.726 line:90% position:50% align:center
And also the Governing Body
is neither inspired nor infallible.

00:06:54.726 --> 00:06:59.731 line:90% position:50% align:center
And so it can err in doctrinal matters
or in organizational direction.

00:06:59.731 --> 00:07:02.567 line:90% position:50% align:center
The brothers do the best they can
with what they have

00:07:02.567 --> 00:07:05.028 line:90% position:50% align:center
and what they understand at the time

00:07:05.028 --> 00:07:09.241 line:90% position:50% align:center
but are happy if Jehovah sees fit
to clarify matters,

00:07:09.241 --> 00:07:11.660 line:90% position:50% align:center
and then that can be shared
with the brotherhood.

00:07:11.660 --> 00:07:13.203 line:90% position:50% align:center
And when that happens,

00:07:13.203 --> 00:07:17.040 line:90% position:50% align:center
we understand it’s because it’s
Jehovah’s time for that to happen,

00:07:17.040 --> 00:07:19.293 line:90% position:50% align:center
and we eagerly accept that.

00:07:21.128 --> 00:07:24.047 line:90% position:50% align:center
But now let’s go back
to our original question.

00:07:24.047 --> 00:07:26.049 line:90% position:50% align:center
OK, we understand these things
from the Scriptures.

00:07:26.049 --> 00:07:27.634 line:90% position:50% align:center
But, really, how does it work?

00:07:27.634 --> 00:07:30.887 line:90% position:50% align:center
When the brothers are meeting together,
how does Jehovah help them

00:07:30.887 --> 00:07:34.224 line:90% position:50% align:center
come to a better understanding of things?

00:07:35.142 --> 00:07:39.354 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, that’s an appropriate question
because Jehovah does not intend for it to be

00:07:39.354 --> 00:07:42.733 line:90% position:50% align:center
a mystery or overly secretive.

00:07:42.733 --> 00:07:45.277 line:90% position:50% align:center
In fact, in his inspired Scriptures,

00:07:45.277 --> 00:07:49.114 line:90% position:50% align:center
he reveals examples of when understanding

00:07:49.114 --> 00:07:51.616 line:90% position:50% align:center
was clarified in the Christian era.

00:07:51.616 --> 00:07:54.870 line:90% position:50% align:center
And a notable example was around 49 C.E.

00:07:54.870 --> 00:07:59.207 line:90% position:50% align:center
when clarification was needed
regarding the requirements for salvation.

00:07:59.207 --> 00:08:01.209 line:90% position:50% align:center
And specifically, the question was this:

00:08:01.209 --> 00:08:04.755 line:90% position:50% align:center
Would Gentile males
first need to be circumcised

00:08:04.755 --> 00:08:08.550 line:90% position:50% align:center
and submit to the Mosaic Law
in order to be saved?

00:08:09.384 --> 00:08:13.472 line:90% position:50% align:center
This was a significant matter that could have
divided the congregation,

00:08:13.472 --> 00:08:15.640 line:90% position:50% align:center
and so it was referred to the apostles

00:08:15.640 --> 00:08:19.853 line:90% position:50% align:center
and the older men, the governing body,
at that time.

00:08:19.853 --> 00:08:22.481 line:90% position:50% align:center
And in fact, at Galatians 2:2,

00:08:22.481 --> 00:08:26.360 line:90% position:50% align:center
Paul states
that “as a result of a revelation,”

00:08:26.360 --> 00:08:29.321 line:90% position:50% align:center
he brought the matter to the brothers
in Jerusalem.

00:08:29.321 --> 00:08:33.700 line:90% position:50% align:center
So Christ himself directed
that this important doctrinal matter

00:08:33.700 --> 00:08:36.703 line:90% position:50% align:center
be settled by the brothers taking the lead.

00:08:36.703 --> 00:08:41.291 line:90% position:50% align:center
And in Acts 15, Jehovah allows us
to look in on that meeting

00:08:41.291 --> 00:08:45.629 line:90% position:50% align:center
(to be a fly on the wall, as it were)
to hear their discussion

00:08:45.629 --> 00:08:50.425 line:90% position:50% align:center
—to see how the holy spirit worked with them,
how they used God’s Word,

00:08:50.425 --> 00:08:53.512 line:90% position:50% align:center
how they came to a conclusion,
and then the result

00:08:53.512 --> 00:08:57.015 line:90% position:50% align:center
that was sent and conveyed
to the congregations.

00:08:57.015 --> 00:09:00.977 line:90% position:50% align:center
And the process
is not entirely different today.

00:09:00.977 --> 00:09:05.190 line:90% position:50% align:center
So let’s take a look at what happened
if we turn together to Acts chapter 15.

00:09:09.361 --> 00:09:12.614 line:90% position:50% align:center
Acts chapter 15 and beginning in verse 6,
it says:

00:09:12.614 --> 00:09:15.784 line:90% position:50% align:center
“The apostles and the elders
gathered together to look into this matter.”

00:09:15.784 --> 00:09:17.494 line:90% position:50% align:center
So this is an important matter.

00:09:17.494 --> 00:09:21.289 line:90% position:50% align:center
It’s brought before the governing body
of that day.

00:09:21.289 --> 00:09:23.667 line:90% position:50% align:center
And then in verse 7,

00:09:23.667 --> 00:09:27.546 line:90% position:50% align:center
it mentions that there was
“much intense discussion.”

00:09:27.546 --> 00:09:29.631 line:90% position:50% align:center
So it was a lively conversation.

00:09:29.631 --> 00:09:33.176 line:90% position:50% align:center
The brothers felt free
to express themselves respectfully,

00:09:33.176 --> 00:09:35.762 line:90% position:50% align:center
but they were sharing
their thoughts and opinions

00:09:35.762 --> 00:09:37.764 line:90% position:50% align:center
about the different sides of the issue.

00:09:37.764 --> 00:09:39.766 line:90% position:50% align:center
And in verse 7, Peter stands.

00:09:39.766 --> 00:09:44.521 line:90% position:50% align:center
And maybe this is the point
that is reflected in our artwork here.

00:09:44.521 --> 00:09:48.150 line:90% position:50% align:center
And Peter begins to speak
and relates his comments

00:09:48.150 --> 00:09:52.195 line:90% position:50% align:center
based on his real-life experience
with Cornelius.

00:09:52.195 --> 00:09:55.449 line:90% position:50% align:center
So they’re considering some facts.

00:09:55.449 --> 00:09:59.327 line:90% position:50% align:center
And if you look in verse 12,
Peter’s words strike a chord

00:09:59.327 --> 00:10:02.789 line:90% position:50% align:center
because “the entire group [becomes] silent.”

00:10:02.789 --> 00:10:05.876 line:90% position:50% align:center
And in this, we see humility
—don’t we?—

00:10:05.876 --> 00:10:08.962 line:90% position:50% align:center
because none of the brothers
were trying to force their personal opinion

00:10:08.962 --> 00:10:11.089 line:90% position:50% align:center
or get their idea approved.

00:10:11.089 --> 00:10:15.594 line:90% position:50% align:center
They were collectively looking to Jehovah
for direction on the matter.

00:10:16.511 --> 00:10:19.181 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, this makes way, then,
for Paul and Barnabas

00:10:19.181 --> 00:10:21.558 line:90% position:50% align:center
to begin to explain their experiences.

00:10:21.558 --> 00:10:25.479 line:90% position:50% align:center
So there were more facts, more evidence,
that they could consider.

00:10:25.479 --> 00:10:28.315 line:90% position:50% align:center
And then in verse 13, James speaks up

00:10:28.315 --> 00:10:31.026 line:90% position:50% align:center
and he uses the Scriptures
to help the brothers

00:10:31.026 --> 00:10:34.321 line:90% position:50% align:center
draw a proper Scriptural conclusion.

00:10:34.321 --> 00:10:37.741 line:90% position:50% align:center
He applies Amos 9:11, 12, saying that Jehovah 

00:10:37.741 --> 00:10:40.160 line:90% position:50% align:center
would turn “his attention to the nations

00:10:40.160 --> 00:10:43.121 line:90% position:50% align:center
to take out of them a people for his name.”

00:10:44.414 --> 00:10:49.419 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well in verses 19-21,
he recommends a decision.

00:10:49.419 --> 00:10:54.049 line:90% position:50% align:center
Verse 25 indicates
that that decision was unanimous.

00:10:54.049 --> 00:10:57.552 line:90% position:50% align:center
And then in verse 22,
it mentions that they sent the brothers out

00:10:57.552 --> 00:11:01.765 line:90% position:50% align:center
to inform the congregation
of this clarified understanding.

00:11:02.724 --> 00:11:06.895 line:90% position:50% align:center
So in the whole process described there,
we see the use of God’s Word,

00:11:06.895 --> 00:11:10.440 line:90% position:50% align:center
we see the leadership of the Christ,
and the operation of the holy spirit

00:11:10.440 --> 00:11:13.902 line:90% position:50% align:center
working through the brothers
taking the lead at that time.

00:11:14.945 --> 00:11:17.989 line:90% position:50% align:center
And so we can see the process is not intended

00:11:17.989 --> 00:11:22.202 line:90% position:50% align:center
to be a mystery or to be overly secretive.

00:11:22.202 --> 00:11:26.915 line:90% position:50% align:center
And the process today
is not much dissimilar than that.

00:11:27.624 --> 00:11:31.169 line:90% position:50% align:center
In 2010,
<i>The Watchtower</i>  explained it this way.

00:11:31.169 --> 00:11:35.674 line:90% position:50% align:center
It said: “When the time comes
to clarify a spiritual matter in our day,

00:11:35.674 --> 00:11:38.593 line:90% position:50% align:center
“holy spirit helps . . .
‘the faithful and discreet slave’ . . .

00:11:38.593 --> 00:11:43.515 line:90% position:50% align:center
“to discern deep truths
that were not previously understood.

00:11:43.515 --> 00:11:48.228 line:90% position:50% align:center
“The Governing Body as a whole
considers adjusted explanations.

00:11:48.228 --> 00:11:52.274 line:90% position:50% align:center
What they learn,
they publish for the benefit of all.”

00:11:53.608 --> 00:11:57.988 line:90% position:50% align:center
So generally the process happens this way:

00:11:57.988 --> 00:12:00.824 line:90% position:50% align:center
First of all, a question comes up.

00:12:00.824 --> 00:12:04.619 line:90% position:50% align:center
And so it could be that a Governing Body
member in his personal study

00:12:04.619 --> 00:12:09.249 line:90% position:50% align:center
or his personal Bible reading notices
something that then raises a question.

00:12:09.249 --> 00:12:12.669 line:90% position:50% align:center
Or it could be that a question
comes up during the preparation

00:12:12.669 --> 00:12:14.754 line:90% position:50% align:center
or translation of spiritual food

00:12:14.754 --> 00:12:18.049 line:90% position:50% align:center
that requires more consideration.

00:12:18.049 --> 00:12:21.553 line:90% position:50% align:center
World events might put the spotlight
on a particular prophecy

00:12:21.553 --> 00:12:24.264 line:90% position:50% align:center
that then gets closer attention.

00:12:24.264 --> 00:12:27.267 line:90% position:50% align:center
So in one way or another,
a question comes up.

00:12:27.267 --> 00:12:29.269 line:90% position:50% align:center
And that question is then put on

00:12:29.269 --> 00:12:32.147 line:90% position:50% align:center
the Governing Body’s agenda for discussion.

00:12:32.147 --> 00:12:33.648 line:90% position:50% align:center
And the question is,

00:12:33.648 --> 00:12:38.653 line:90% position:50% align:center
Does this require, or warrant,

00:12:38.653 --> 00:12:40.780 line:90% position:50% align:center
additional research?

00:12:40.780 --> 00:12:44.409 line:90% position:50% align:center
The brothers are not making a final decision
on what the new understanding will be

00:12:44.409 --> 00:12:48.371 line:90% position:50% align:center
but are just asking,
“Does it warrant additional research?”

00:12:48.371 --> 00:12:52.709 line:90% position:50% align:center
And if the answer is yes,
then a research team is assigned to provide

00:12:52.709 --> 00:12:57.505 line:90% position:50% align:center
recommendations and research
for the Governing Body to consider.

00:12:57.505 --> 00:13:01.384 line:90% position:50% align:center
And this research includes
a summary of everything that we have said

00:13:01.384 --> 00:13:05.221 line:90% position:50% align:center
(the organization has said)
on the subject since 1879

00:13:05.221 --> 00:13:08.183 line:90% position:50% align:center
—all of <i>The Watchtowers </i>
on what we have said.

00:13:08.183 --> 00:13:13.188 line:90% position:50% align:center
Also, it includes what the context
of the verse indicates about its meaning.

00:13:14.105 --> 00:13:17.400 line:90% position:50% align:center
Further, what bearing do parallel accounts

00:13:17.400 --> 00:13:22.322 line:90% position:50% align:center
have on the understanding of the account,
if there are any parallel accounts?

00:13:22.322 --> 00:13:26.117 line:90% position:50% align:center
And finally, what impact
does the original Hebrew or Greek

00:13:26.117 --> 00:13:28.953 line:90% position:50% align:center
have on our understanding of the verse?

00:13:29.871 --> 00:13:32.916 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, once that whole research package
is compiled,

00:13:32.916 --> 00:13:37.087 line:90% position:50% align:center
it’s placed back on
the Governing Body’s agenda for review.

00:13:37.087 --> 00:13:39.089 line:90% position:50% align:center
And, of course, once it goes on the agenda,

00:13:39.089 --> 00:13:42.300 line:90% position:50% align:center
then each individual member
of the Governing Body under prayer

00:13:42.300 --> 00:13:46.888 line:90% position:50% align:center
reviews the information and thinks about it
in preparation for the meeting.

00:13:46.888 --> 00:13:49.015 line:90% position:50% align:center
And then it’s discussed as a group

00:13:49.015 --> 00:13:52.018 line:90% position:50% align:center
at the Governing Body meeting
again under prayer,

00:13:52.018 --> 00:13:55.522 line:90% position:50% align:center
relying on Jehovah’s holy spirit.

00:13:55.522 --> 00:13:58.942 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, when this matter is discussed,
the discussion is not rushed,

00:13:58.942 --> 00:14:01.486 line:90% position:50% align:center
nor is the decision forced.

00:14:01.486 --> 00:14:04.739 line:90% position:50% align:center
But often, like in the first century,
it’s a lively discussion

00:14:04.739 --> 00:14:08.034 line:90% position:50% align:center
as the brothers feel free to share
their opinions and their thoughts

00:14:08.034 --> 00:14:11.830 line:90% position:50% align:center
and the results of their meditation
and their research.

00:14:11.830 --> 00:14:16.000 line:90% position:50% align:center
But there’s also humility there
because, again, none of the brothers

00:14:16.000 --> 00:14:20.255 line:90% position:50% align:center
are trying to force their idea
or are trying to get their thoughts approved.

00:14:20.255 --> 00:14:24.092 line:90% position:50% align:center
But there is this collective, unified desire

00:14:24.092 --> 00:14:29.097 line:90% position:50% align:center
to see Jehovah’s direction on the matter
and where he is steering things.

00:14:29.097 --> 00:14:33.101 line:90% position:50% align:center
The goal is to discern Jehovah’s direction
on the matter.

00:14:33.101 --> 00:14:35.645 line:90% position:50% align:center
And often (or at times, we could say),

00:14:35.645 --> 00:14:38.189 line:90% position:50% align:center
the final result might be quite different

00:14:38.189 --> 00:14:41.234 line:90% position:50% align:center
than what the research package
originally recommended.

00:14:41.234 --> 00:14:44.863 line:90% position:50% align:center
But that’s Jehovah’s spirit working
through “the faithful and discreet slave”

00:14:44.863 --> 00:14:47.532 line:90% position:50% align:center
to bring us to the right decision.

00:14:47.532 --> 00:14:51.119 line:90% position:50% align:center
And the brothers
are looking for a unanimous decision.

00:14:51.119 --> 00:14:54.080 line:90% position:50% align:center
At times, it may seem like this
is a solid adjustment,

00:14:54.080 --> 00:14:56.082 line:90% position:50% align:center
but if it’s not unanimous,

00:14:56.082 --> 00:15:00.003 line:90% position:50% align:center
it just might not be time yet
for it to be revealed.

00:15:00.003 --> 00:15:01.421 line:90% position:50% align:center
And so it’s not forced.

00:15:01.421 --> 00:15:03.256 line:90% position:50% align:center
The matter is set aside.

00:15:03.256 --> 00:15:06.342 line:90% position:50% align:center
And it could be that sometime later,
even some years later,

00:15:06.342 --> 00:15:09.929 line:90% position:50% align:center
the matter comes back up
and then it sails right through.

00:15:09.929 --> 00:15:13.850 line:90% position:50% align:center
Or maybe it does get approved
but now with a couple of key points

00:15:13.850 --> 00:15:16.770 line:90% position:50% align:center
discerned that weren’t discerned earlier.

00:15:18.021 --> 00:15:21.524 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, with this thorough process under prayer

00:15:21.524 --> 00:15:23.777 line:90% position:50% align:center
and when there is unanimous accord,

00:15:23.777 --> 00:15:26.613 line:90% position:50% align:center
then the brothers
take that as Jehovah’s direction

00:15:26.613 --> 00:15:29.115 line:90% position:50% align:center
and then are happy to share it
with the brotherhood.

00:15:31.409 --> 00:15:34.329 line:90% position:50% align:center
So this helps us to understand the process,

00:15:34.329 --> 00:15:38.833 line:90% position:50% align:center
understand how light
gets brighter in modern times.

00:15:39.876 --> 00:15:42.253 line:90% position:50% align:center
And while it is interesting to us

00:15:42.253 --> 00:15:45.673 line:90% position:50% align:center
how our understanding is clarified,

00:15:45.673 --> 00:15:49.928 line:90% position:50% align:center
what really touches our heart
is why it’s clarified.

00:15:50.887 --> 00:15:54.390 line:90% position:50% align:center
Turn with me, please,
to the book of Amos chapter 3.

00:15:58.394 --> 00:16:01.439 line:90% position:50% align:center
And notice what Amos 3:7 says:

00:16:03.858 --> 00:16:06.903 line:90% position:50% align:center
“For the Sovereign Lord Jehovah
will not do a thing

00:16:06.903 --> 00:16:10.198 line:90% position:50% align:center
“unless he has revealed
his confidential matter

00:16:10.198 --> 00:16:12.492 line:90% position:50% align:center
to his servants the prophets.”

00:16:13.493 --> 00:16:17.038 line:90% position:50% align:center
Doesn’t that convey
Jehovah’s confidence in us?

00:16:17.038 --> 00:16:21.584 line:90% position:50% align:center
Doesn’t it indicate his love and his loyalty?

00:16:21.584 --> 00:16:25.088 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehovah is actively involved
in teaching his people,

00:16:25.088 --> 00:16:28.132 line:90% position:50% align:center
preparing us for what lies ahead.

00:16:28.132 --> 00:16:32.971 line:90% position:50% align:center
He’s providing us with the understanding
that we need when we need it.

00:16:32.971 --> 00:16:36.474 line:90% position:50% align:center
And that is reassuring
—isn’t it?—

00:16:36.474 --> 00:16:40.228 line:90% position:50% align:center
because as we progress
deeper into the time of the end,

00:16:40.228 --> 00:16:43.064 line:90% position:50% align:center
as Satan’s hatred intensifies

00:16:43.064 --> 00:16:45.650 line:90% position:50% align:center
and his attacks increase,

00:16:45.650 --> 00:16:48.152 line:90% position:50% align:center
as we draw closer to the great tribulation

00:16:48.152 --> 00:16:51.698 line:90% position:50% align:center
and the destruction
of Satan’s wicked system of things,

00:16:51.698 --> 00:16:55.785 line:90% position:50% align:center
we can be confident that Jehovah God,
our God,

00:16:55.785 --> 00:16:57.996 line:90% position:50% align:center
will continue to loyally provide us

00:16:57.996 --> 00:17:01.833 line:90% position:50% align:center
with the direction and the understanding
that we need.

00:17:01.833 --> 00:17:06.754 line:90% position:50% align:center
We will not be left without guidance,
unsure where to go or what to do.

00:17:06.754 --> 00:17:09.549 line:90% position:50% align:center
We will not be left to stumble in the dark

00:17:09.549 --> 00:17:11.718 line:90% position:50% align:center
because Jehovah has said:

00:17:11.718 --> 00:17:16.222 line:90% position:50% align:center
“The path of the righteous one
is like the bright morning light

00:17:16.222 --> 00:17:19.809 line:90% position:50% align:center
that grows brighter and brighter
until full daylight.”

00:17:33.740 --> 00:17:35.909 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, with these things in mind,

00:17:35.909 --> 00:17:39.621 line:90% position:50% align:center
I invite you to listen closely
to the next two talks.

00:17:39.621 --> 00:17:42.373 line:90% position:50% align:center
The first will be presented
by Brother David Splane

00:17:42.373 --> 00:17:46.794 line:90% position:50% align:center
and is entitled “Trust in the Merciful
‘Judge of All the Earth.’”

00:17:48.755 --> 00:17:51.382 line:90% position:50% align:center
By means of an angel,

00:17:53.009 --> 00:17:56.888 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehovah God told his dear friend Abraham

00:17:56.888 --> 00:18:01.392 line:90% position:50% align:center
that he was going to destroy
the cities of Sodom and Gomorrah.

00:18:01.809 --> 00:18:03.895 line:90% position:50% align:center
The angel said:

00:18:03.895 --> 00:18:06.397 line:90% position:50% align:center
“The outcry against Sodom and Gomorrah

00:18:06.397 --> 00:18:09.108 line:90% position:50% align:center
“is indeed great,

00:18:09.108 --> 00:18:13.071 line:90% position:50% align:center
and their sin is very heavy.”

00:18:15.573 --> 00:18:17.617 line:90% position:50% align:center
Abraham was troubled.

00:18:18.242 --> 00:18:19.994 line:90% position:50% align:center
He apparently wondered

00:18:19.994 --> 00:18:23.581 line:90% position:50% align:center
whether Jehovah had taken
all of the factors into consideration

00:18:23.581 --> 00:18:27.502 line:90% position:50% align:center
before he made that decision
to destroy the cities.

00:18:28.378 --> 00:18:30.755 line:90% position:50% align:center
So he asked:

00:18:30.755 --> 00:18:35.218 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Will the Judge of all the earth
not do what is right?”

00:18:37.136 --> 00:18:41.766 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, we can understand
why Abraham would ask that question.

00:18:42.433 --> 00:18:46.813 line:90% position:50% align:center
It was early days
in his relationship with Jehovah God.

00:18:46.813 --> 00:18:51.401 line:90% position:50% align:center
He was just beginning
to get acquainted with Jehovah,

00:18:51.401 --> 00:18:54.946 line:90% position:50% align:center
and we can hardly imagine him
asking the same question later

00:18:54.946 --> 00:18:57.115 line:90% position:50% align:center
when he knew Jehovah much better.

00:18:58.700 --> 00:19:03.037 line:90% position:50% align:center
But have you ever asked a similar question,

00:19:03.037 --> 00:19:05.957 line:90% position:50% align:center
maybe when you
were just coming into the truth?

00:19:06.874 --> 00:19:08.960 line:90% position:50% align:center
Have you ever asked, for example:

00:19:08.960 --> 00:19:13.506 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Will none of those
who died in the Flood get a resurrection

00:19:13.506 --> 00:19:17.468 line:90% position:50% align:center
“—even those
who may never have heard of Noah?

00:19:17.468 --> 00:19:19.846 line:90% position:50% align:center
“And what about Sodom and Gomorrah?

00:19:21.264 --> 00:19:23.891 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Will everyone who died
in Sodom and Gomorrah

00:19:23.891 --> 00:19:26.686 line:90% position:50% align:center
“sleep an everlasting sleep

00:19:26.686 --> 00:19:31.315 line:90% position:50% align:center
“—the women, the children, the babies?

00:19:32.525 --> 00:19:37.530 line:90% position:50% align:center
“And was there not one
redeemable Assyrian soldier

00:19:38.114 --> 00:19:42.410 line:90% position:50% align:center
“in that band of 185,000 who died

00:19:42.410 --> 00:19:44.537 line:90% position:50% align:center
at the hand of Jehovah’s angel?”

00:19:46.247 --> 00:19:48.958 line:90% position:50% align:center
We don’t have the answer to those questions.

00:19:50.084 --> 00:19:52.086 line:90% position:50% align:center
But we do know one thing:

00:19:53.087 --> 00:19:58.092 line:90% position:50% align:center
The merciful “Judge of all the earth”
will do what is right.

00:19:59.552 --> 00:20:01.596 line:90% position:50% align:center
Wait a minute.

00:20:01.596 --> 00:20:03.681 line:90% position:50% align:center
Did I hear that right?

00:20:04.182 --> 00:20:07.226 line:90% position:50% align:center
We don’t have the answer to those questions?

00:20:07.810 --> 00:20:09.771 line:90% position:50% align:center
I thought we did.

00:20:10.188 --> 00:20:12.857 line:90% position:50% align:center
In the past, our publications have stated

00:20:12.857 --> 00:20:15.359 line:90% position:50% align:center
that there’s no hope of a resurrection

00:20:15.359 --> 00:20:19.864 line:90% position:50% align:center
for those who died in the Flood
or those destroyed in Sodom and Gomorrah.

00:20:21.157 --> 00:20:23.326 line:90% position:50% align:center
But do we really know that?

00:20:24.744 --> 00:20:27.789 line:90% position:50% align:center
The men of Sodom and Gomorrah
were certainly wicked,

00:20:27.789 --> 00:20:30.500 line:90% position:50% align:center
and they deserved to die for what they did.

00:20:31.167 --> 00:20:35.379 line:90% position:50% align:center
But did they know any better?

00:20:36.214 --> 00:20:39.884 line:90% position:50% align:center
How often
did Lot and his family preach to them?

00:20:39.884 --> 00:20:42.720 line:90% position:50% align:center
And are we saying that if special pioneers

00:20:42.720 --> 00:20:45.098 line:90% position:50% align:center
had been assigned to Sodom,

00:20:45.098 --> 00:20:49.727 line:90% position:50% align:center
they would have had no success whatsoever
in preaching to the Sodomites,

00:20:49.727 --> 00:20:53.314 line:90% position:50% align:center
helping them to turn around
and come to a knowledge of Jehovah?

00:20:54.440 --> 00:20:56.442 line:90% position:50% align:center
Can we say dogmatically

00:20:56.442 --> 00:20:59.737 line:90% position:50% align:center
that not one Sodomite would have repented

00:20:59.737 --> 00:21:03.282 line:90% position:50% align:center
if Jehovah’s requirements had been explained?

00:21:04.325 --> 00:21:07.036 line:90% position:50% align:center
And then there’s the fascinating statement

00:21:07.036 --> 00:21:10.623 line:90% position:50% align:center
made by Jesus found in Matthew chapter 11

00:21:12.792 --> 00:21:17.130 line:90% position:50% align:center
—I’ll give you a moment—Matthew chapter 11.

00:21:17.130 --> 00:21:21.217 line:90% position:50% align:center
And we’re going to read verses 23 and 24.

00:21:23.553 --> 00:21:25.596 line:90% position:50% align:center
This is interesting

00:21:26.722 --> 00:21:30.434 line:90% position:50% align:center
—Matthew 11:23, 24:

00:21:31.727 --> 00:21:36.941 line:90% position:50% align:center
“And you, Capernaum,
will you perhaps be exalted to heaven?

00:21:36.941 --> 00:21:39.152 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Down to the Grave you will come;

00:21:39.152 --> 00:21:42.572 line:90% position:50% align:center
“because [and notice this]
if the powerful works

00:21:42.572 --> 00:21:46.993 line:90% position:50% align:center
“that took place in you
had taken place in Sodom,

00:21:46.993 --> 00:21:51.455 line:90% position:50% align:center
“it would have remained until this very day.

00:21:51.455 --> 00:21:53.499 line:90% position:50% align:center
“But I say to you

00:21:53.499 --> 00:21:58.421 line:90% position:50% align:center
“it will be more endurable
for the land of Sodom on Judgment Day

00:21:58.421 --> 00:22:00.840 line:90% position:50% align:center
than for you.”

00:22:00.840 --> 00:22:04.385 line:90% position:50% align:center
“It would have remained

00:22:04.385 --> 00:22:07.305 line:90% position:50% align:center
until this very day.”

00:22:07.305 --> 00:22:11.100 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehovah’s angel had told Abraham

00:22:11.100 --> 00:22:14.520 line:90% position:50% align:center
that if ten righteous men
could be found in Sodom,

00:22:14.520 --> 00:22:16.397 line:90% position:50% align:center
the city would not be destroyed.

00:22:16.397 --> 00:22:20.526 line:90% position:50% align:center
So was Jesus saying
that if he had preached

00:22:20.526 --> 00:22:23.654 line:90% position:50% align:center
and performed powerful works in Sodom,

00:22:23.654 --> 00:22:27.658 line:90% position:50% align:center
ten righteous men would have been found

00:22:27.658 --> 00:22:29.911 line:90% position:50% align:center
and the city would have been spared?

00:22:30.703 --> 00:22:32.705 line:90% position:50% align:center
It’s also of interest

00:22:32.705 --> 00:22:36.459 line:90% position:50% align:center
to consider Jehovah’s words
to unfaithful Judah

00:22:36.459 --> 00:22:38.961 line:90% position:50% align:center
in Ezekiel chapter 16.

00:22:38.961 --> 00:22:42.089 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehovah said that the citizens of Sodom

00:22:42.089 --> 00:22:45.259 line:90% position:50% align:center
were more righteous
than the inhabitants of Judah.

00:22:45.259 --> 00:22:49.222 line:90% position:50% align:center
So if Sodom is doomed, what about Judah?

00:22:51.182 --> 00:22:53.517 line:90% position:50% align:center
But what about the disciple Jude’s statement

00:22:53.517 --> 00:22:55.311 line:90% position:50% align:center
that Sodom and Gomorrah would undergo

00:22:55.311 --> 00:22:58.814 line:90% position:50% align:center
“the judicial punishment
of everlasting fire”?

00:22:59.315 --> 00:23:02.401 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, that certainly
will prove true of the cities

00:23:02.401 --> 00:23:05.363 line:90% position:50% align:center
and probably many of the inhabitants as well,

00:23:05.363 --> 00:23:09.033 line:90% position:50% align:center
but does it mean
that there’s no hope for any of them?

00:23:09.033 --> 00:23:11.577 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jesus’ statement we just read

00:23:11.577 --> 00:23:13.621 line:90% position:50% align:center
would indicate that there is hope for some.

00:23:14.705 --> 00:23:18.292 line:90% position:50% align:center
We just can’t be dogmatic.

00:23:19.085 --> 00:23:24.090 line:90% position:50% align:center
But again, we can say
that the merciful “Judge of all the earth”

00:23:24.090 --> 00:23:26.300 line:90% position:50% align:center
will do what is right.

00:23:27.134 --> 00:23:30.179 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now let’s talk about the Flood of Noah’s day.

00:23:30.179 --> 00:23:33.099 line:90% position:50% align:center
In the past, we’ve said that any
who died in the Flood

00:23:33.099 --> 00:23:35.101 line:90% position:50% align:center
would not be resurrected.

00:23:35.643 --> 00:23:37.645 line:90% position:50% align:center
But does the Bible say that?

00:23:38.354 --> 00:23:41.357 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, Noah’s contemporaries
certainly were wicked,

00:23:41.357 --> 00:23:44.652 line:90% position:50% align:center
and the Bible says that “man’s wickedness
was great on the earth

00:23:44.652 --> 00:23:47.780 line:90% position:50% align:center
“and that every inclination
of the thoughts of his heart

00:23:47.780 --> 00:23:50.283 line:90% position:50% align:center
was only bad all the time.”

00:23:50.950 --> 00:23:54.954 line:90% position:50% align:center
So those living at that time were sinners,

00:23:54.954 --> 00:23:58.124 line:90% position:50% align:center
but did they all get a thorough witness?

00:23:59.083 --> 00:24:02.670 line:90% position:50% align:center
Noah and his family
must have been very busy building the ark.

00:24:02.670 --> 00:24:06.215 line:90% position:50% align:center
How much time did they have for preaching?

00:24:06.215 --> 00:24:10.011 line:90% position:50% align:center
And were they able
to do seldom-worked territory?

00:24:11.595 --> 00:24:14.890 line:90% position:50% align:center
We have found that people
who live within ten miles (16 km) of Bethel

00:24:14.890 --> 00:24:17.476 line:90% position:50% align:center
have never heard of Jehovah’s Witnesses.

00:24:17.476 --> 00:24:21.605 line:90% position:50% align:center
So can we guarantee
that everyone living on earth

00:24:21.605 --> 00:24:25.192 line:90% position:50% align:center
during that time knew of Noah
and what he was doing?

00:24:25.192 --> 00:24:27.236 line:90% position:50% align:center
We can’t really say that.

00:24:27.236 --> 00:24:31.991 line:90% position:50% align:center
And can we say that if someone
had been given an adequate opportunity, 

00:24:31.991 --> 00:24:35.953 line:90% position:50% align:center
he still would have turned
his back on Jehovah?

00:24:35.953 --> 00:24:38.289 line:90% position:50% align:center
We just can’t say that.

00:24:39.206 --> 00:24:41.959 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, of course,
if Jehovah didn’t bring them back,

00:24:41.959 --> 00:24:44.378 line:90% position:50% align:center
they wouldn’t have any grounds for complaint.

00:24:45.129 --> 00:24:47.131 line:90% position:50% align:center
They’ve had life,

00:24:47.131 --> 00:24:51.510 line:90% position:50% align:center
and life is more than any of us deserves.

00:24:51.510 --> 00:24:54.096 line:90% position:50% align:center
As you know, when Adam and Eve sinned,

00:24:54.096 --> 00:24:56.140 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehovah could have destroyed
them right away.

00:24:56.140 --> 00:25:00.353 line:90% position:50% align:center
But instead, he gave them the opportunity
to have sons and daughters.

00:25:00.353 --> 00:25:03.272 line:90% position:50% align:center
And as a result, we were born.

00:25:03.272 --> 00:25:06.108 line:90% position:50% align:center
So the fact that you and I

00:25:06.108 --> 00:25:09.111 line:90% position:50% align:center
have drawn one breath

00:25:09.111 --> 00:25:13.240 line:90% position:50% align:center
is pure undeserved kindness
on Jehovah’s part.

00:25:14.950 --> 00:25:17.536 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, on the other hand,
for many years it was suggested

00:25:17.536 --> 00:25:21.499 line:90% position:50% align:center
that all those who the Bible says
were buried with their forefathers

00:25:21.499 --> 00:25:23.542 line:90% position:50% align:center
were going to have a resurrection.

00:25:24.251 --> 00:25:26.712 line:90% position:50% align:center
Solomon was one of those.

00:25:26.712 --> 00:25:28.589 line:90% position:50% align:center
The Bible says of him:

00:25:28.589 --> 00:25:33.260 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Then Solomon was laid to rest
with his forefathers

00:25:33.260 --> 00:25:36.889 line:90% position:50% align:center
and was buried
in the City of David his father.”

00:25:37.765 --> 00:25:41.644 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, we reasoned that those
who were buried with their forefathers

00:25:41.644 --> 00:25:43.187 line:90% position:50% align:center
were in the common grave of mankind,

00:25:43.187 --> 00:25:46.482 line:90% position:50% align:center
and we know that the common grave
of mankind is going to be emptied

00:25:46.482 --> 00:25:48.901 line:90% position:50% align:center
during the Thousand Year Reign of Christ.

00:25:49.902 --> 00:25:52.613 line:90% position:50% align:center
But we ask ourselves:

00:25:53.447 --> 00:25:57.576 line:90% position:50% align:center
‘When Bible writers said that someone
was buried with his forefathers,

00:25:57.576 --> 00:26:01.914 line:90% position:50% align:center
‘were they really revealing
what Jehovah’s final judgment would be?

00:26:01.914 --> 00:26:05.042 line:90% position:50% align:center
‘Was Jehovah revealing to them
—inspiring them to say—

00:26:05.042 --> 00:26:08.254 line:90% position:50% align:center
‘how he was going to settle the case?

00:26:08.254 --> 00:26:10.756 line:90% position:50% align:center
‘Or were the Bible writers really saying

00:26:10.756 --> 00:26:13.592 line:90% position:50% align:center
‘that this is the way the person was buried

00:26:13.592 --> 00:26:15.970 line:90% position:50% align:center
—this is the manner of his burial?’

00:26:15.970 --> 00:26:18.931 line:90% position:50% align:center
Remember, in Bible times,
the way someone was buried

00:26:18.931 --> 00:26:21.100 line:90% position:50% align:center
was very important.

00:26:21.100 --> 00:26:25.896 line:90% position:50% align:center
Joseph and Jacob
refused to be buried in Egypt.

00:26:25.896 --> 00:26:29.608 line:90% position:50% align:center
High Priest Jehoiada
was buried with the kings of Judah

00:26:29.608 --> 00:26:32.069 line:90% position:50% align:center
because of all the good things he had done.

00:26:32.903 --> 00:26:35.281 line:90% position:50% align:center
And when a prophet said that a certain king

00:26:35.281 --> 00:26:38.951 line:90% position:50% align:center
was going to have “the burial of a donkey,”
that wasn’t good.

00:26:41.162 --> 00:26:45.958 line:90% position:50% align:center
Solomon was the second wisest man
ever to walk the earth.

00:26:46.792 --> 00:26:49.879 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehovah appeared to him twice,
and the second time he appeared to him,

00:26:49.879 --> 00:26:54.592 line:90% position:50% align:center
he said: “If you and your sons
turn away from following me

00:26:54.592 --> 00:26:58.637 line:90% position:50% align:center
“and . . . you go and serve other gods
and bow down to them,

00:26:58.637 --> 00:27:03.225 line:90% position:50% align:center
I will cut Israel off
from the surface of the land.”

00:27:04.226 --> 00:27:06.687 line:90% position:50% align:center
What did Solomon do?

00:27:07.646 --> 00:27:11.484 line:90% position:50% align:center
He began to “serve other gods
and bow down to them.”

00:27:12.526 --> 00:27:15.613 line:90% position:50% align:center
How will
the “Judge of all the earth” view that?

00:27:16.739 --> 00:27:18.741 line:90% position:50% align:center
That’s not for us to say.

00:27:19.366 --> 00:27:21.827 line:90% position:50% align:center
So we can’t be dogmatic about the prospects

00:27:21.827 --> 00:27:24.788 line:90% position:50% align:center
of those who are said to be buried
with their forefathers.

00:27:24.788 --> 00:27:26.499 line:90% position:50% align:center
It could be that the Bible

00:27:26.499 --> 00:27:30.377 line:90% position:50% align:center
was just indicating
the manner of their burial.

00:27:30.377 --> 00:27:33.255 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, that isn’t to say
that they won’t be resurrected.

00:27:33.255 --> 00:27:36.675 line:90% position:50% align:center
It simply means that we don’t know.

00:27:37.468 --> 00:27:41.639 line:90% position:50% align:center
The righteous Judge knows,
and we know that he’ll do the right thing.

00:27:43.015 --> 00:27:45.809 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, what do we know about Jehovah?

00:27:46.519 --> 00:27:48.896 line:90% position:50% align:center
Why can we trust him to do the right thing?

00:27:49.438 --> 00:27:51.482 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, look at the record.

00:27:51.482 --> 00:27:53.484 line:90% position:50% align:center
In the days of the prophet Joel,

00:27:53.484 --> 00:27:57.321 line:90% position:50% align:center
God’s people
were in a sick spiritual condition.

00:27:57.321 --> 00:28:02.076 line:90% position:50% align:center
They were worshipping the Baals
and the golden calves and the sacred poles.

00:28:02.076 --> 00:28:04.495 line:90% position:50% align:center
They were lying,
committing adultery, stealing,

00:28:04.495 --> 00:28:07.831 line:90% position:50% align:center
shedding innocent blood,
oppressing widows and orphans.

00:28:08.457 --> 00:28:11.627 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehovah had good reason
to wipe the whole nation out.

00:28:11.627 --> 00:28:14.255 line:90% position:50% align:center
And yet, what do we read at Joel 2:13?

00:28:14.255 --> 00:28:17.633 line:90% position:50% align:center
Joel says: “Rip apart your hearts,

00:28:17.633 --> 00:28:21.637 line:90% position:50% align:center
“and not your garments,
and return to Jehovah your God,

00:28:21.637 --> 00:28:24.557 line:90% position:50% align:center
“for he is compassionate and merciful,

00:28:24.557 --> 00:28:27.851 line:90% position:50% align:center
“slow to anger and abundant in loyal love,

00:28:27.851 --> 00:28:32.356 line:90% position:50% align:center
and he will reconsider the calamity.”

00:28:34.233 --> 00:28:38.237 line:90% position:50% align:center
“He will reconsider the calamity.”

00:28:38.237 --> 00:28:42.408 line:90% position:50% align:center
After all that,
Jehovah was willing to show mercy.

00:28:43.158 --> 00:28:45.327 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, this is very encouraging.

00:28:46.203 --> 00:28:48.038 line:90% position:50% align:center
Why?

00:28:49.123 --> 00:28:52.334 line:90% position:50% align:center
Many of our brothers
have no trouble accepting the fact

00:28:52.334 --> 00:28:57.256 line:90% position:50% align:center
that Jehovah will forgive the sins
they committed in their ignorance

00:28:57.256 --> 00:28:59.758 line:90% position:50% align:center
before they came to a knowledge of the truth.

00:29:01.594 --> 00:29:05.598 line:90% position:50% align:center
But if they’ve committed a sin after baptism,

00:29:05.598 --> 00:29:09.893 line:90% position:50% align:center
they’re afraid that Jehovah will never forget
and he will never forgive them.

00:29:09.893 --> 00:29:11.562 line:90% position:50% align:center
And yet, what do we see here?

00:29:11.562 --> 00:29:16.191 line:90% position:50% align:center
The nation of Israel
was in a dedicated situation before Jehovah,

00:29:16.191 --> 00:29:19.653 line:90% position:50% align:center
and yet Jehovah said:
‘If you stop doing what is wrong

00:29:19.653 --> 00:29:24.158 line:90% position:50% align:center
and if you start doing what is right,
I will reconsider.’

00:29:25.367 --> 00:29:28.954 line:90% position:50% align:center
Then you have the encouraging words
found in Ezekiel chapter 33.

00:29:28.954 --> 00:29:30.998 line:90% position:50% align:center
Let’s read this.

00:29:33.500 --> 00:29:38.380 line:90% position:50% align:center
I find that this is a good passage to read
to brothers and sisters

00:29:38.380 --> 00:29:42.426 line:90% position:50% align:center
who may feel that Jehovah could never
forgive them for what they’ve done.

00:29:42.426 --> 00:29:46.597 line:90% position:50% align:center
Ezekiel 33:14, 16

00:29:49.642 --> 00:29:51.685 line:90% position:50% align:center
—verse 14 first:

00:29:52.686 --> 00:29:55.356 line:90% position:50% align:center
“And when I say to the wicked one:

00:29:55.356 --> 00:29:57.566 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘You will surely die,’

00:29:57.566 --> 00:30:01.236 line:90% position:50% align:center
“and he turns away from his sin

00:30:01.236 --> 00:30:04.365 line:90% position:50% align:center
“and does what is just and righteous, . . .

00:30:04.365 --> 00:30:05.949 line:90% position:50% align:center
“[verse 16]

00:30:05.949 --> 00:30:09.870 line:90% position:50% align:center
“none of the sins he committed
will be held against him.

00:30:09.870 --> 00:30:13.040 line:90% position:50% align:center
“For doing what is just and righteous,

00:30:13.040 --> 00:30:16.335 line:90% position:50% align:center
he will surely keep living.”

00:30:17.086 --> 00:30:21.465 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, isn’t that encouraging
for someone who strayed from the truth,

00:30:21.465 --> 00:30:24.009 line:90% position:50% align:center
maybe got involved in some bad conduct?

00:30:24.009 --> 00:30:27.054 line:90% position:50% align:center
Far too many of these ones

00:30:27.054 --> 00:30:30.182 line:90% position:50% align:center
are afraid that Jehovah
will never forgive them.

00:30:30.182 --> 00:30:33.352 line:90% position:50% align:center
They would love to come back to the truth,
and they would love to come back to Jehovah,

00:30:33.352 --> 00:30:36.647 line:90% position:50% align:center
but they’re afraid that Jehovah
is not going to accept them.

00:30:36.647 --> 00:30:38.273 line:90% position:50% align:center
And yet he says:

00:30:38.273 --> 00:30:42.945 line:90% position:50% align:center
“None of the sins he committed
will be held against him.”

00:30:43.654 --> 00:30:45.989 line:90% position:50% align:center
The case of King Manasseh makes the point.

00:30:45.989 --> 00:30:48.409 line:90% position:50% align:center
He was in a dedicated relationship
with Jehovah,

00:30:48.409 --> 00:30:52.162 line:90% position:50% align:center
and yet for most of his life,
he did what was wrong.

00:30:52.162 --> 00:30:55.582 line:90% position:50% align:center
But when he repented, turned around,

00:30:55.582 --> 00:30:57.626 line:90% position:50% align:center
and started doing what was right,

00:30:57.626 --> 00:31:00.295 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehovah wiped the slate clean.

00:31:00.963 --> 00:31:05.300 line:90% position:50% align:center
What a marvelous, merciful God we worship!

00:31:06.468 --> 00:31:09.430 line:90% position:50% align:center
It shows that Jehovah will show mercy

00:31:09.430 --> 00:31:12.349 line:90% position:50% align:center
whenever he sees a basis for doing so.

00:31:13.183 --> 00:31:16.645 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, consider how Jehovah
dealt with the people of Nineveh

00:31:16.645 --> 00:31:18.272 line:90% position:50% align:center
in the days of Jonah.

00:31:18.272 --> 00:31:20.774 line:90% position:50% align:center
Their conduct was so bad

00:31:20.774 --> 00:31:23.819 line:90% position:50% align:center
that Jehovah was determined
to destroy the city,

00:31:23.819 --> 00:31:25.821 line:90% position:50% align:center
and Jonah was in agreement with that.

00:31:25.821 --> 00:31:27.865 line:90% position:50% align:center
‘Yeah, wipe them all out.’

00:31:28.615 --> 00:31:33.036 line:90% position:50% align:center
But Jehovah was more merciful
than Jonah was,

00:31:33.036 --> 00:31:36.665 line:90% position:50% align:center
and when He saw
that the people repented and turned around,

00:31:36.665 --> 00:31:38.500 line:90% position:50% align:center
He was willing to forgive them.

00:31:38.500 --> 00:31:40.878 line:90% position:50% align:center
Why?
The Bible tells us why.

00:31:41.795 --> 00:31:45.090 line:90% position:50% align:center
They didn’t “know right from wrong.”

00:31:47.134 --> 00:31:50.137 line:90% position:50% align:center
They didn’t know any better.

00:31:50.137 --> 00:31:52.723 line:90% position:50% align:center
Will some of those Ninevites be back?

00:31:52.723 --> 00:31:56.310 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jesus’ words found at Matthew 12:41

00:31:56.310 --> 00:31:58.228 line:90% position:50% align:center
seem to indicate that they will.

00:31:58.228 --> 00:32:02.691 line:90% position:50% align:center
He said: “Men of Nineveh
will rise up in the judgment

00:32:02.691 --> 00:32:05.819 line:90% position:50% align:center
“with this generation and will condemn it,

00:32:05.819 --> 00:32:08.781 line:90% position:50% align:center
“because they repented
at what Jonah preached.

00:32:08.781 --> 00:32:12.701 line:90% position:50% align:center
But look! something more than Jonah is here.”

00:32:13.619 --> 00:32:16.538 line:90% position:50% align:center
So, what do we see from these examples?

00:32:16.538 --> 00:32:21.335 line:90% position:50% align:center
The men of Nineveh, Manasseh, and others

00:32:21.335 --> 00:32:24.546 line:90% position:50% align:center
—they were wicked, they did bad things,

00:32:24.546 --> 00:32:28.425 line:90% position:50% align:center
they repented,
they started to do what was right,

00:32:28.425 --> 00:32:31.720 line:90% position:50% align:center
and Jehovah wiped the slate clean.

00:32:32.971 --> 00:32:36.850 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, today, power for judging
has been given to someone else.

00:32:36.850 --> 00:32:39.978 line:90% position:50% align:center
There’s a different judge of all the earth.

00:32:39.978 --> 00:32:43.357 line:90% position:50% align:center
And we read about him in John chapter 5

00:32:47.110 --> 00:32:49.112 line:90% position:50% align:center
—John chapter 5—

00:32:49.905 --> 00:32:51.740 line:90% position:50% align:center
and we’re going to read verse 22.

00:32:51.740 --> 00:32:53.575 line:90% position:50% align:center
I’ll give you a moment.

00:32:55.494 --> 00:32:57.538 line:90% position:50% align:center
John 5:22:

00:32:59.540 --> 00:33:03.001 line:90% position:50% align:center
“For the Father judges no one at all,

00:33:03.001 --> 00:33:07.297 line:90% position:50% align:center
“but he has entrusted all the judging

00:33:07.297 --> 00:33:11.176 line:90% position:50% align:center
[all the judging] to the Son.”

00:33:11.176 --> 00:33:16.181 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jesus has been given authority
“to judge the living and the dead.”

00:33:16.849 --> 00:33:19.142 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, can we trust him?

00:33:19.142 --> 00:33:21.728 line:90% position:50% align:center
Can we be sure that Jesus will be merciful?

00:33:21.728 --> 00:33:22.980 line:90% position:50% align:center
Absolutely!

00:33:22.980 --> 00:33:25.649 line:90% position:50% align:center
He’s the exact image of his Father,

00:33:25.649 --> 00:33:28.402 line:90% position:50% align:center
and the prophet Isaiah wrote of him:

00:33:28.402 --> 00:33:31.947 line:90% position:50% align:center
“He will not judge
by what appears to his eyes,

00:33:31.947 --> 00:33:35.868 line:90% position:50% align:center
“nor reprove
simply according to what his ears hear.

00:33:35.868 --> 00:33:38.078 line:90% position:50% align:center
“He will judge the lowly with fairness,

00:33:38.078 --> 00:33:41.039 line:90% position:50% align:center
“and with uprightness he will give reproof

00:33:41.039 --> 00:33:43.834 line:90% position:50% align:center
in behalf of the meek ones of the earth.”

00:33:45.085 --> 00:33:50.090 line:90% position:50% align:center
The authority that Jesus has been given
includes the authority to resurrect the dead.

00:33:50.757 --> 00:33:53.385 line:90% position:50% align:center
He’s “the resurrection and the life.”

00:33:53.677 --> 00:33:55.470 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, you know, we often say

00:33:55.470 --> 00:33:59.141 line:90% position:50% align:center
that Jehovah God knows everything
about those who have died,

00:33:59.141 --> 00:34:01.184 line:90% position:50% align:center
and that’s true.

00:34:01.184 --> 00:34:03.854 line:90% position:50% align:center
But since Jesus is doing the resurrecting,

00:34:03.854 --> 00:34:07.900 line:90% position:50% align:center
it’s reasonable to conclude
that he also knows everything

00:34:07.900 --> 00:34:10.652 line:90% position:50% align:center
about the dead and the living,

00:34:10.652 --> 00:34:14.406 line:90% position:50% align:center
and he is going to be able
to resurrect them accurately.

00:34:14.406 --> 00:34:16.408 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, whether he’ll share
the power to resurrect

00:34:16.408 --> 00:34:19.077 line:90% position:50% align:center
with his anointed brothers
when they’re raised to heaven

00:34:19.077 --> 00:34:21.121 line:90% position:50% align:center
remains to be seen.

00:34:21.121 --> 00:34:23.165 line:90% position:50% align:center
We’ll stay tuned.

00:34:23.749 --> 00:34:27.628 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, what’s the takeaway
from this talk so far?

00:34:27.628 --> 00:34:31.340 line:90% position:50% align:center
How would you explain it
to someone who wasn’t here today?

00:34:31.340 --> 00:34:33.342 line:90% position:50% align:center
You would not say,

00:34:33.342 --> 00:34:35.427 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Some who died in Sodom and Gomorrah

00:34:35.427 --> 00:34:37.429 line:90% position:50% align:center
“and in the Flood
are going to be resurrected,

00:34:37.429 --> 00:34:39.181 line:90% position:50% align:center
and Solomon isn’t going to be resurrected.”

00:34:39.181 --> 00:34:41.224 line:90% position:50% align:center
No, no, no.
You wouldn’t say that.

00:34:42.434 --> 00:34:46.855 line:90% position:50% align:center
What we’re saying
is that we shouldn’t be dogmatic

00:34:46.855 --> 00:34:50.776 line:90% position:50% align:center
about who will
and who will not be resurrected.

00:34:50.776 --> 00:34:53.278 line:90% position:50% align:center
We just don’t know.

00:34:53.278 --> 00:34:55.280 line:90% position:50% align:center
But we trust Jehovah God,

00:34:55.280 --> 00:34:57.783 line:90% position:50% align:center
we trust Jesus Christ,

00:34:57.783 --> 00:35:00.786 line:90% position:50% align:center
and they will do what is right.

00:35:03.455 --> 00:35:05.499 line:90% position:50% align:center
I know what you’re thinking.

00:35:06.708 --> 00:35:10.796 line:90% position:50% align:center
The wheels are turning,
and you’re saying to yourself:

00:35:10.796 --> 00:35:11.922 line:90% position:50% align:center
‘Come on, come on.

00:35:11.922 --> 00:35:14.132 line:90% position:50% align:center
‘We’ve talked about the Flood,

00:35:14.132 --> 00:35:16.635 line:90% position:50% align:center
‘we’ve talked about Sodom and Gomorrah,

00:35:16.635 --> 00:35:19.262 line:90% position:50% align:center
‘but what about the great tribulation?

00:35:19.262 --> 00:35:23.517 line:90% position:50% align:center
Is there anything
that we can or can’t say about that?’

00:35:23.517 --> 00:35:25.560 line:90% position:50% align:center
You know, that’s a good question.

00:35:25.560 --> 00:35:27.562 line:90% position:50% align:center
We should talk about that.

00:35:28.563 --> 00:35:30.941 line:90% position:50% align:center
You know what?
I think my time is up.

00:35:47.290 --> 00:35:50.585 line:90% position:50% align:center
It looks like I have to finish
Brother Splane’s talk.

00:35:52.045 --> 00:35:55.382 line:90% position:50% align:center
And I don’t think you want me
to talk about anything else.

00:35:56.675 --> 00:36:01.138 line:90% position:50% align:center
So, what is the takeaway point
up to this time?

00:36:01.138 --> 00:36:03.640 line:90% position:50% align:center
I’m sure we got the point.

00:36:03.640 --> 00:36:07.561 line:90% position:50% align:center
It’s helped us to think about our loving,
heavenly Father, Jehovah,

00:36:07.561 --> 00:36:11.356 line:90% position:50% align:center
as the merciful Judge of the entire earth,

00:36:11.356 --> 00:36:13.608 line:90% position:50% align:center
and his Son, Jesus Christ.

00:36:13.608 --> 00:36:16.153 line:90% position:50% align:center
Yes, we can trust them

00:36:16.153 --> 00:36:19.156 line:90% position:50% align:center
to make proper judgments.

00:36:19.156 --> 00:36:23.035 line:90% position:50% align:center
We know that Jehovah
and Jesus can read hearts.

00:36:23.035 --> 00:36:25.328 line:90% position:50% align:center
And they have a long record

00:36:25.328 --> 00:36:29.791 line:90% position:50% align:center
of living by the perfect standards of justice
that Jehovah has set up.

00:36:30.584 --> 00:36:33.754 line:90% position:50% align:center
So, what about the future judgments

00:36:33.754 --> 00:36:35.839 line:90% position:50% align:center
during the great tribulation?

00:36:35.839 --> 00:36:40.385 line:90% position:50% align:center
Is there something that we can adjust
with regard to our understanding?

00:36:40.385 --> 00:36:45.057 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, before we start to do that,
let’s be quite frank.

00:36:45.057 --> 00:36:47.809 line:90% position:50% align:center
Over the last few years,
we’ve had a few changes

00:36:47.809 --> 00:36:51.813 line:90% position:50% align:center
with regard to the events
that occur during the great tribulation.

00:36:51.813 --> 00:36:54.024 line:90% position:50% align:center
And if you’ve been in the truth for a while,

00:36:54.024 --> 00:36:56.026 line:90% position:50% align:center
sometimes it’s a bit hard to remember,

00:36:56.026 --> 00:37:00.447 line:90% position:50% align:center
‘Was that what we used to believe,
or is this what we believe now?’

00:37:01.198 --> 00:37:05.410 line:90% position:50% align:center
So to help us to make sure
that we’ve got some idea

00:37:05.410 --> 00:37:09.581 line:90% position:50% align:center
of some of the events
that occur during the great tribulation,

00:37:09.581 --> 00:37:11.792 line:90% position:50% align:center
let’s look at this review.

00:37:15.837 --> 00:37:18.215 line:90% position:50% align:center
What event starts the great tribulation?

00:37:19.007 --> 00:37:21.676 line:90% position:50% align:center
The destruction of Babylon the Great.

00:37:21.676 --> 00:37:24.679 line:90% position:50% align:center
That will be the time
when the political powers

00:37:24.679 --> 00:37:27.182 line:90% position:50% align:center
turn on the world empire of false religion,

00:37:27.182 --> 00:37:31.061 line:90% position:50% align:center
showing their disgust
for the symbolic prostitute.

00:37:31.061 --> 00:37:33.563 line:90% position:50% align:center
This will lead to the destruction

00:37:33.563 --> 00:37:36.066 line:90% position:50% align:center
of all false religious organizations.

00:37:38.193 --> 00:37:41.321 line:90% position:50% align:center
What event ends the great tribulation?

00:37:41.321 --> 00:37:43.698 line:90% position:50% align:center
The battle of Armageddon.

00:37:43.698 --> 00:37:47.494 line:90% position:50% align:center
That will be the final part
of the great tribulation.

00:37:47.494 --> 00:37:51.748 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jesus, along with the resurrected 144,000

00:37:51.748 --> 00:37:54.126 line:90% position:50% align:center
and myriads of angels, will battle

00:37:54.126 --> 00:37:56.378 line:90% position:50% align:center
with all those who oppose Jehovah,

00:37:56.378 --> 00:37:59.840 line:90% position:50% align:center
his Kingdom, and his people here on earth.

00:37:59.840 --> 00:38:03.677 line:90% position:50% align:center
This will be “the war
of the great day of God the Almighty.”

00:38:05.804 --> 00:38:07.973 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now that we have the start

00:38:07.973 --> 00:38:10.642 line:90% position:50% align:center
and the end of the great tribulation in mind,

00:38:10.642 --> 00:38:13.353 line:90% position:50% align:center
let’s ask a few more questions.

00:38:13.353 --> 00:38:15.772 line:90% position:50% align:center
How long will that time period be

00:38:15.772 --> 00:38:17.816 line:90% position:50% align:center
from start to finish?

00:38:17.816 --> 00:38:21.027 line:90% position:50% align:center
The answer is we don’t know.

00:38:21.027 --> 00:38:23.446 line:90% position:50% align:center
We do know that many events

00:38:23.446 --> 00:38:26.283 line:90% position:50% align:center
are foretold to happen during that time period.

00:38:26.283 --> 00:38:28.618 line:90% position:50% align:center
But these events may all occur

00:38:28.618 --> 00:38:31.705 line:90% position:50% align:center
in a reasonably short period of time.

00:38:31.705 --> 00:38:33.707 line:90% position:50% align:center
For this discussion, though,

00:38:33.707 --> 00:38:36.459 line:90% position:50% align:center
let’s focus on the few events that will occur

00:38:36.459 --> 00:38:39.087 line:90% position:50% align:center
toward the end of the great tribulation.

00:38:40.172 --> 00:38:44.092 line:90% position:50% align:center
When does the attack of Gog of Magog occur?

00:38:44.092 --> 00:38:47.846 line:90% position:50% align:center
It doesn’t occur at the beginning
of the great tribulation

00:38:47.846 --> 00:38:51.016 line:90% position:50% align:center
but toward the end of that period of time.

00:38:51.016 --> 00:38:54.477 line:90% position:50% align:center
This attack on God’s people
by a coalition of nations

00:38:54.477 --> 00:38:57.522 line:90% position:50% align:center
will lead right
into the battle of Armageddon.

00:38:57.522 --> 00:39:01.943 line:90% position:50% align:center
So Gog’s attack will occur
just prior to Armageddon.

00:39:03.612 --> 00:39:06.531 line:90% position:50% align:center
When will the remaining ones of the anointed

00:39:06.531 --> 00:39:09.326 line:90% position:50% align:center
be gathered and taken to heaven?

00:39:09.326 --> 00:39:11.786 line:90% position:50% align:center
The Bible book of Ezekiel indicates

00:39:11.786 --> 00:39:14.623 line:90% position:50% align:center
that when Gog of Magog starts his attack,

00:39:14.623 --> 00:39:19.002 line:90% position:50% align:center
some of the anointed
will still be here on earth.

00:39:19.002 --> 00:39:22.631 line:90% position:50% align:center
However, Revelation 17:14 tells us

00:39:22.631 --> 00:39:25.217 line:90% position:50% align:center
that when Jesus battles with the nations,

00:39:25.217 --> 00:39:29.054 line:90% position:50% align:center
he will come with those
“who are called and chosen,”

00:39:29.054 --> 00:39:33.308 line:90% position:50% align:center
that is, all of the resurrected 144,000.

00:39:35.435 --> 00:39:39.522 line:90% position:50% align:center
So the final gathering
of his chosen ones must occur

00:39:39.522 --> 00:39:42.692 line:90% position:50% align:center
after the start of the attack of Gog of Magog

00:39:42.692 --> 00:39:45.779 line:90% position:50% align:center
and before the battle of Armageddon.

00:39:45.779 --> 00:39:49.741 line:90% position:50% align:center
This means that the anointed
will be gathered and taken to heaven

00:39:49.741 --> 00:39:54.120 line:90% position:50% align:center
toward the end of the great tribulation,
not at the beginning.

00:39:55.956 --> 00:40:00.418 line:90% position:50% align:center
When will the final judgment
of the sheep and the goats take place?

00:40:00.418 --> 00:40:03.004 line:90% position:50% align:center
Again, although we can’t be dogmatic

00:40:03.004 --> 00:40:05.632 line:90% position:50% align:center
as to the exact sequence of events,

00:40:05.632 --> 00:40:08.677 line:90% position:50% align:center
it appears
that the final judgment takes place

00:40:08.677 --> 00:40:11.263 line:90% position:50% align:center
at the end of the great tribulation,

00:40:11.263 --> 00:40:13.265 line:90% position:50% align:center
not at the beginning.

00:40:13.265 --> 00:40:16.935 line:90% position:50% align:center
That will be the time
“when the Son of man comes in his glory,

00:40:16.935 --> 00:40:19.229 line:90% position:50% align:center
and all [his] angels with him.”

00:40:19.229 --> 00:40:22.440 line:90% position:50% align:center
Of course, there are a lot of other events

00:40:22.440 --> 00:40:25.568 line:90% position:50% align:center
that are foretold to happen
during this time period,

00:40:25.568 --> 00:40:29.531 line:90% position:50% align:center
but for now,
let’s just focus on these few events,

00:40:29.531 --> 00:40:34.160 line:90% position:50% align:center
all of which will happen
just before the outbreak of Armageddon.

00:40:35.745 --> 00:40:37.872 line:90% position:50% align:center
What do we learn from them?

00:40:37.872 --> 00:40:41.334 line:90% position:50% align:center
First, Jesus’ judgment
of the sheep and the goats

00:40:41.334 --> 00:40:43.378 line:90% position:50% align:center
and the destruction of the wicked

00:40:43.378 --> 00:40:47.299 line:90% position:50% align:center
will take place
at the end of the great tribulation.

00:40:47.299 --> 00:40:50.719 line:90% position:50% align:center
Second, there will be some
of the remaining ones

00:40:50.719 --> 00:40:52.721 line:90% position:50% align:center
of the anointed on earth

00:40:52.721 --> 00:40:55.682 line:90% position:50% align:center
until the start
of the attack of Gog of Magog,

00:40:55.682 --> 00:40:59.060 line:90% position:50% align:center
right at the end of the great tribulation.

00:40:59.060 --> 00:41:01.396 line:90% position:50% align:center
Third, the judgment

00:41:01.396 --> 00:41:02.856 line:90% position:50% align:center
of the sheep and the goats

00:41:02.856 --> 00:41:04.274 line:90% position:50% align:center
will include their dealings

00:41:04.274 --> 00:41:05.900 line:90% position:50% align:center
with Christ’s brothers,

00:41:05.900 --> 00:41:08.695 line:90% position:50% align:center
even during the great tribulation.

00:41:14.200 --> 00:41:18.079 line:90% position:50% align:center
So that is a review
of what we already believe.

00:41:18.079 --> 00:41:20.790 line:90% position:50% align:center
So if you were writing down notes
(“oh, that’s a new point”),

00:41:20.790 --> 00:41:22.834 line:90% position:50% align:center
be careful what you say to others.

00:41:24.711 --> 00:41:27.213 line:90% position:50% align:center
But how do these basic facts

00:41:27.213 --> 00:41:29.215 line:90% position:50% align:center
(when we look at the things that occur

00:41:29.215 --> 00:41:32.552 line:90% position:50% align:center
toward the end of the great tribulation,
how do they)

00:41:32.552 --> 00:41:34.888 line:90% position:50% align:center
affect our understanding

00:41:34.888 --> 00:41:39.017 line:90% position:50% align:center
of Jehovah’s judgments
by means of Jesus Christ?

00:41:39.017 --> 00:41:42.979 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, we know that the closer
we get to the great tribulation,

00:41:42.979 --> 00:41:47.150 line:90% position:50% align:center
the clearer our understanding
is of what will occur.

00:41:47.150 --> 00:41:51.821 line:90% position:50% align:center
Yes, our understanding is clarified
according to the proper time

00:41:51.821 --> 00:41:56.451 line:90% position:50% align:center
and also in a way that will help us
not only to endure the great tribulation

00:41:56.451 --> 00:42:00.622 line:90% position:50% align:center
but also to prosper
during that period of time.

00:42:00.622 --> 00:42:02.624 line:90% position:50% align:center
So, what we’re going to do

00:42:02.624 --> 00:42:07.087 line:90% position:50% align:center
is consider four very interesting questions.

00:42:10.382 --> 00:42:12.634 line:90% position:50% align:center
Yes, and I’ve got some time left.

00:42:14.052 --> 00:42:16.554 line:90% position:50% align:center
The first question is,

00:42:16.554 --> 00:42:19.432 line:90% position:50% align:center
Once the great tribulation starts

00:42:19.432 --> 00:42:21.643 line:90% position:50% align:center
(we saw there in the chart

00:42:21.643 --> 00:42:26.064 line:90% position:50% align:center
with the destruction of Babylon the Great,
so once it starts),

00:42:26.064 --> 00:42:29.692 line:90% position:50% align:center
is there a door of opportunity

00:42:29.692 --> 00:42:33.780 line:90% position:50% align:center
for nonbelievers to actually join us

00:42:33.780 --> 00:42:35.990 line:90% position:50% align:center
in serving Jehovah?

00:42:35.990 --> 00:42:38.576 line:90% position:50% align:center
Is there a door of opportunity?

00:42:38.576 --> 00:42:41.037 line:90% position:50% align:center
What have we said in the past?

00:42:41.037 --> 00:42:45.708 line:90% position:50% align:center
We’ve said,
“No, there will not be an opportunity

00:42:45.708 --> 00:42:48.211 line:90% position:50% align:center
for people to join us at that time.”

00:42:48.211 --> 00:42:50.463 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, why did we say that?

00:42:50.463 --> 00:42:53.591 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, basically,
we viewed the account of the Flood

00:42:53.591 --> 00:42:57.303 line:90% position:50% align:center
as being a type and antitype portrayal.

00:42:57.303 --> 00:43:02.308 line:90% position:50% align:center
And we thought the fact
that the door of the ark was closed

00:43:02.308 --> 00:43:04.602 line:90% position:50% align:center
prior to the Flood coming

00:43:04.602 --> 00:43:09.149 line:90% position:50% align:center
indicated that the door of opportunity
would close

00:43:09.149 --> 00:43:11.609 line:90% position:50% align:center
once the great tribulation started.

00:43:12.735 --> 00:43:17.740 line:90% position:50% align:center
But, of course, it’s true;
Jesus did compare the time of Noah

00:43:17.740 --> 00:43:22.745 line:90% position:50% align:center
with the presence of him as a reigning King.

00:43:22.745 --> 00:43:25.665 line:90% position:50% align:center
But notice, Jesus didn’t say anything

00:43:25.665 --> 00:43:28.835 line:90% position:50% align:center
that indicated
this was a type-antitype arrangement,

00:43:28.835 --> 00:43:31.337 line:90% position:50% align:center
and he certainly didn’t mention

00:43:31.337 --> 00:43:36.217 line:90% position:50% align:center
anything with regard
to a door of opportunity closing.

00:43:36.217 --> 00:43:39.345 line:90% position:50% align:center
So let’s think about that question again.

00:43:39.345 --> 00:43:42.724 line:90% position:50% align:center
Once the great tribulation starts,

00:43:42.724 --> 00:43:45.935 line:90% position:50% align:center
is there a door of opportunity still available?

00:43:45.935 --> 00:43:49.063 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, to answer that, looking at this time chart,

00:43:49.063 --> 00:43:51.065 line:90% position:50% align:center
remember, the judgment

00:43:51.065 --> 00:43:53.109 line:90% position:50% align:center
of the sheep and the goats

00:43:53.109 --> 00:43:55.278 line:90% position:50% align:center
—the final judgment—occurs when?

00:43:55.278 --> 00:43:57.447 line:90% position:50% align:center
Not at the beginning,

00:43:57.447 --> 00:44:01.326 line:90% position:50% align:center
but toward the end of the great tribulation.

00:44:02.410 --> 00:44:05.288 line:90% position:50% align:center
So let’s think about some whom we know

00:44:05.288 --> 00:44:10.251 line:90% position:50% align:center
—perhaps unbelieving relatives,
disfellowshipped ones,

00:44:10.251 --> 00:44:14.130 line:90% position:50% align:center
others who have heard the message
and perhaps have studied with us.

00:44:14.130 --> 00:44:16.424 line:90% position:50% align:center
Could some of them,

00:44:16.424 --> 00:44:20.512 line:90% position:50% align:center
once they see the destruction
of Babylon the Great,

00:44:20.512 --> 00:44:24.432 line:90% position:50% align:center
decide that what Jehovah’s Witnesses
were saying

00:44:24.432 --> 00:44:26.684 line:90% position:50% align:center
is correct after all?

00:44:26.684 --> 00:44:30.396 line:90% position:50% align:center
Could they take a stand for the truth?

00:44:30.396 --> 00:44:35.193 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, if they changed
their hearts and joined us,

00:44:35.193 --> 00:44:37.487 line:90% position:50% align:center
would we be disappointed?

00:44:38.780 --> 00:44:40.782 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, we can’t be dogmatic,

00:44:42.200 --> 00:44:45.828 line:90% position:50% align:center
but we don’t want to be like Jonah

00:44:45.828 --> 00:44:50.708 line:90% position:50% align:center
and say: “Oh, no, no.
The door is closed, no, no.”

00:44:52.043 --> 00:44:56.297 line:90% position:50% align:center
You see, we need to remember
other cases in the Scriptures that help us

00:44:56.297 --> 00:44:59.425 line:90% position:50% align:center
to understand how Jehovah as a merciful Judge

00:44:59.425 --> 00:45:01.928 line:90% position:50% align:center
has dealt with people in the past.

00:45:01.928 --> 00:45:05.598 line:90% position:50% align:center
For example, think about the Israelites
when they left Egypt.

00:45:05.598 --> 00:45:07.684 line:90% position:50% align:center
Please, if you turn with me

00:45:07.684 --> 00:45:10.895 line:90% position:50% align:center
to Exodus chapter 12,

00:45:10.895 --> 00:45:13.189 line:90% position:50% align:center
Exodus chapter 12,

00:45:13.189 --> 00:45:16.359 line:90% position:50% align:center
and we’re going to read
the first part of verse 38.

00:45:16.359 --> 00:45:19.571 line:90% position:50% align:center
So here it’s describing the Exodus,

00:45:19.571 --> 00:45:22.574 line:90% position:50% align:center
and Exodus 12:38 says:

00:45:22.574 --> 00:45:25.827 line:90% position:50% align:center
“And a vast mixed company

00:45:25.827 --> 00:45:27.996 line:90% position:50% align:center
also went with them.”

00:45:27.996 --> 00:45:30.456 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now—do you notice?—
there’s a footnote there.

00:45:30.456 --> 00:45:32.083 line:90% position:50% align:center
And what does it say?

00:45:32.083 --> 00:45:36.462 line:90% position:50% align:center
“That is, a mixed company of non-Israelites,

00:45:36.462 --> 00:45:38.840 line:90% position:50% align:center
including Egyptians.”

00:45:39.966 --> 00:45:42.427 line:90% position:50% align:center
So, what happened?

00:45:42.427 --> 00:45:47.307 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, during the time when the Ten Plagues
came upon the Egyptians,

00:45:47.307 --> 00:45:49.809 line:90% position:50% align:center
obviously some of these Egyptians

00:45:49.809 --> 00:45:52.270 line:90% position:50% align:center
started to see the distinction

00:45:52.270 --> 00:45:56.399 line:90% position:50% align:center
between Jehovah and the false gods
that they worshipped.

00:45:56.399 --> 00:45:59.068 line:90% position:50% align:center
So when decision time came

00:45:59.068 --> 00:46:01.779 line:90% position:50% align:center
and the Israelites were leaving Egypt,

00:46:01.779 --> 00:46:05.575 line:90% position:50% align:center
some of these Egyptians
joined the Israelites.

00:46:05.575 --> 00:46:08.202 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, isn’t that interesting for us to note?

00:46:09.412 --> 00:46:12.290 line:90% position:50% align:center
But, of course, we might be thinking:

00:46:12.290 --> 00:46:16.461 line:90% position:50% align:center
‘Yes, well, I understand why
we said what we did before,

00:46:16.461 --> 00:46:21.299 line:90% position:50% align:center
‘but is it really the case
that all these ones whom we’ve studied with

00:46:21.299 --> 00:46:24.218 line:90% position:50% align:center
‘or so on (some of them) may have a chance

00:46:24.218 --> 00:46:27.347 line:90% position:50% align:center
‘to join us after Babylon the Great
is destroyed?

00:46:27.347 --> 00:46:29.349 line:90% position:50% align:center
‘Is that fair?

00:46:30.475 --> 00:46:33.269 line:90% position:50% align:center
Last-minute repentance.’

00:46:34.854 --> 00:46:39.859 line:90% position:50% align:center
But, you see, are we imitating
the merciful “Judge of all the earth”?

00:46:40.735 --> 00:46:44.656 line:90% position:50% align:center
Really, we shouldn’t be surprised
if that were to happen, should we?

00:46:44.656 --> 00:46:46.491 line:90% position:50% align:center
And think about it.

00:46:46.491 --> 00:46:50.828 line:90% position:50% align:center
As we looked at the time chart,
we saw that this is

00:46:50.828 --> 00:46:54.290 line:90% position:50% align:center
a time period prior to the final judgment.

00:46:54.290 --> 00:46:59.295 line:90% position:50% align:center
So anyone who takes their stand for Jehovah
early in the great tribulation

00:46:59.295 --> 00:47:02.173 line:90% position:50% align:center
will still face the attack of Gog of Magog,

00:47:02.173 --> 00:47:04.967 line:90% position:50% align:center
and that will be a very, very difficult time.

00:47:05.760 --> 00:47:09.263 line:90% position:50% align:center
But now, what do we need to note
with regard to this?

00:47:09.263 --> 00:47:14.185 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, just as in the first century,
in 66 C.E.,

00:47:14.185 --> 00:47:16.479 line:90% position:50% align:center
decision time came

00:47:16.479 --> 00:47:21.484 line:90% position:50% align:center
and many decided to go
and leave Jerusalem at that point.

00:47:21.484 --> 00:47:24.028 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, they made their decision

00:47:24.028 --> 00:47:28.032 line:90% position:50% align:center
based on what they already knew
and had heard.

00:47:28.032 --> 00:47:30.243 line:90% position:50% align:center
So, in a similar way,

00:47:30.243 --> 00:47:34.038 line:90% position:50% align:center
our preaching work today
is of utmost importance.

00:47:34.038 --> 00:47:36.666 line:90% position:50% align:center
Let’s notice what the apostle Paul said,

00:47:36.666 --> 00:47:39.419 line:90% position:50% align:center
as recorded in the book of Romans

00:47:39.419 --> 00:47:44.257 line:90% position:50% align:center
—Romans 10:13, 14.

00:47:44.257 --> 00:47:46.092 line:90% position:50% align:center
And as we read this,

00:47:46.092 --> 00:47:49.262 line:90% position:50% align:center
think about the context
of what we’re talking about

00:47:49.262 --> 00:47:52.807 line:90% position:50% align:center
—when Babylon the Great is destroyed.

00:47:52.807 --> 00:47:57.645 line:90% position:50% align:center
So the time prior to that,
we see it says in verse 13:

00:47:57.645 --> 00:48:02.483 line:90% position:50% align:center
“For ‘everyone who calls
on the name of Jehovah will be saved.’

00:48:02.483 --> 00:48:05.778 line:90% position:50% align:center
“However, how will they call on him

00:48:05.778 --> 00:48:08.406 line:90% position:50% align:center
“if they have not put faith in him?

00:48:08.406 --> 00:48:11.701 line:90% position:50% align:center
“How, in turn, will they put faith in him

00:48:11.701 --> 00:48:14.370 line:90% position:50% align:center
“about whom they have not heard?

00:48:14.370 --> 00:48:17.623 line:90% position:50% align:center
“How, in turn, will they hear

00:48:17.623 --> 00:48:20.293 line:90% position:50% align:center
without someone to preach?”

00:48:21.210 --> 00:48:25.882 line:90% position:50% align:center
Do you see why our preaching work
is so urgent and important today?

00:48:26.549 --> 00:48:31.387 line:90% position:50% align:center
Yes, many take the opportunity
to make a decision right now.

00:48:32.305 --> 00:48:36.809 line:90% position:50% align:center
But could it be that once
the great tribulation starts,

00:48:36.809 --> 00:48:39.854 line:90% position:50% align:center
many who have heard the message

00:48:39.854 --> 00:48:42.356 line:90% position:50% align:center
that Jehovah’s Witnesses have preached

00:48:42.356 --> 00:48:44.567 line:90% position:50% align:center
may be in a position then

00:48:44.567 --> 00:48:47.945 line:90% position:50% align:center
to make the right decision, the right choice?

00:48:47.945 --> 00:48:50.364 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, again, we can’t be dogmatic,

00:48:50.364 --> 00:48:54.243 line:90% position:50% align:center
but we certainly hope
that that would be the case.

00:48:54.243 --> 00:48:58.080 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, while we’re talking about this,
let’s talk about the elephant in the room.

00:48:58.080 --> 00:48:59.791 line:90% position:50% align:center
Hmm, what do we mean?

00:48:59.791 --> 00:49:02.210 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, you know, some of us in the past

00:49:02.210 --> 00:49:07.256 line:90% position:50% align:center
(we’re not going to mention names,
but yet some of us) have said:

00:49:07.256 --> 00:49:10.301 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Oh, you know, my unbelieving relative—

00:49:10.301 --> 00:49:13.179 line:90% position:50% align:center
I hope he dies before the great tribulation.”

00:49:13.179 --> 00:49:15.598 line:90% position:50% align:center
Aha!
We know what you’ve been saying.

00:49:17.141 --> 00:49:19.894 line:90% position:50% align:center
We’ve said: “Because if he dies
before the great tribulation,

00:49:19.894 --> 00:49:22.396 line:90% position:50% align:center
“he’ll have a chance of a resurrection.

00:49:22.396 --> 00:49:24.398 line:90% position:50% align:center
But during?
Uh-uh.”

00:49:25.900 --> 00:49:28.277 line:90% position:50% align:center
But let’s think about that.

00:49:28.277 --> 00:49:32.073 line:90% position:50% align:center
You see, does someone’s eternal salvation

00:49:32.073 --> 00:49:35.034 line:90% position:50% align:center
depend on when they die?

00:49:35.034 --> 00:49:39.163 line:90% position:50% align:center
Or does it depend on,
really, their heart condition?

00:49:39.163 --> 00:49:42.458 line:90% position:50% align:center
You see, the merciful Judge of the earth

00:49:42.458 --> 00:49:44.877 line:90% position:50% align:center
knows their heart condition.

00:49:44.877 --> 00:49:48.089 line:90% position:50% align:center
And, really, what are we thinking
if we ask that question?

00:49:48.089 --> 00:49:52.426 line:90% position:50% align:center
You know, are we imagining Jehovah
saying to Jesus: “Look, at this person.

00:49:52.426 --> 00:49:54.846 line:90% position:50% align:center
“You know, they really should die forever.

00:49:54.846 --> 00:49:56.264 line:90% position:50% align:center
“But look at it!

00:49:56.264 --> 00:49:58.266 line:90% position:50% align:center
“They died now before the great tribulation.

00:49:58.266 --> 00:50:00.268 line:90% position:50% align:center
Oh, no!
We have to resurrect them”?

00:50:01.853 --> 00:50:03.312 line:90% position:50% align:center
I mean, really?

00:50:05.106 --> 00:50:09.527 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehovah is the righteous, merciful Judge.

00:50:09.527 --> 00:50:11.529 line:90% position:50% align:center
He knows people’s hearts.

00:50:11.529 --> 00:50:13.531 line:90% position:50% align:center
You can’t fool him or trick him.

00:50:14.448 --> 00:50:18.661 line:90% position:50% align:center
So that was the first question
I’m sure you found interesting, yeah?

00:50:18.661 --> 00:50:21.622 line:90% position:50% align:center
Once the great tribulation starts,

00:50:21.622 --> 00:50:24.166 line:90% position:50% align:center
does the door of opportunity close?

00:50:24.166 --> 00:50:26.544 line:90% position:50% align:center
The answer is, well,
we’ll have to wait and see.

00:50:26.544 --> 00:50:28.671 line:90% position:50% align:center
But according to the Scriptures,

00:50:28.671 --> 00:50:33.217 line:90% position:50% align:center
it is a possibility that some
can take a stand for the truth.

00:50:33.217 --> 00:50:35.219 line:90% position:50% align:center
Second question:

00:50:35.219 --> 00:50:39.599 line:90% position:50% align:center
When does the preaching
of the good news of the Kingdom finish?

00:50:40.349 --> 00:50:42.101 line:90% position:50% align:center
Good question.

00:50:42.101 --> 00:50:44.103 line:90% position:50% align:center
For a start, let’s remember

00:50:44.103 --> 00:50:48.441 line:90% position:50% align:center
that the good news is only good news
to us and to those who accept it.

00:50:48.441 --> 00:50:51.444 line:90% position:50% align:center
As Psalm 2 mentions, though,
for the rest of the world,

00:50:51.444 --> 00:50:54.572 line:90% position:50% align:center
it’s never been good news, has it?

00:50:54.572 --> 00:50:58.409 line:90% position:50% align:center
So, what does Matthew 24:14 tell us?

00:50:58.409 --> 00:51:01.662 line:90% position:50% align:center
It tells us that ‘the good news
is going to be preached,’

00:51:01.662 --> 00:51:05.791 line:90% position:50% align:center
and “then the end will come.”

00:51:05.791 --> 00:51:07.793 line:90% position:50% align:center
Let’s look at our timeline again.

00:51:08.461 --> 00:51:12.048 line:90% position:50% align:center
What is “the end” referred to there?

00:51:12.048 --> 00:51:15.676 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, it’s the final part of the great tribulation.

00:51:16.510 --> 00:51:19.513 line:90% position:50% align:center
So that means that during the great tribulation,

00:51:19.513 --> 00:51:21.140 line:90% position:50% align:center
the good news of the Kingdom

00:51:21.140 --> 00:51:22.600 line:90% position:50% align:center
will still be preached.

00:51:22.600 --> 00:51:25.186 line:90% position:50% align:center
And it’s still good news to us

00:51:25.186 --> 00:51:28.439 line:90% position:50% align:center
but not to the rest of the world.

00:51:28.439 --> 00:51:30.441 line:90% position:50% align:center
That good news will become

00:51:30.441 --> 00:51:33.861 line:90% position:50% align:center
more hard-hitting as time goes on,

00:51:33.861 --> 00:51:37.782 line:90% position:50% align:center
causing people to make
a decision one way or the other,

00:51:37.782 --> 00:51:40.910 line:90% position:50% align:center
whether they accept the Kingdom or not.

00:51:41.786 --> 00:51:45.873 line:90% position:50% align:center
So isn’t that yet another reason
why we shouldn’t be surprised

00:51:45.873 --> 00:51:48.834 line:90% position:50% align:center
that some may take a stand for the truth

00:51:48.834 --> 00:51:50.878 line:90% position:50% align:center
even during the great tribulation?

00:51:52.046 --> 00:51:53.673 line:90% position:50% align:center
The third question:

00:51:54.632 --> 00:51:58.761 line:90% position:50% align:center
All those who die
during the great tribulation,

00:51:58.761 --> 00:52:01.305 line:90% position:50% align:center
will they go into eternal death

00:52:01.305 --> 00:52:03.849 line:90% position:50% align:center
and never be resurrected?

00:52:05.017 --> 00:52:08.562 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, initially, we can say the goats

00:52:08.562 --> 00:52:10.690 line:90% position:50% align:center
are not going to be resurrected
—are they?—

00:52:10.690 --> 00:52:14.151 line:90% position:50% align:center
because they’re
going to “everlasting cutting off,”

00:52:14.151 --> 00:52:16.278 line:90% position:50% align:center
according to what Jesus said.

00:52:16.278 --> 00:52:18.781 line:90% position:50% align:center
And in 2 Thessalonians chapter 1,

00:52:18.781 --> 00:52:22.785 line:90% position:50% align:center
it speaks of the “punishment
of everlasting destruction”

00:52:22.785 --> 00:52:24.829 line:90% position:50% align:center
being meted out.

00:52:24.829 --> 00:52:27.331 line:90% position:50% align:center
But what time period are we talking about?

00:52:27.331 --> 00:52:29.458 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, let’s look at our timeline again.

00:52:29.458 --> 00:52:33.045 line:90% position:50% align:center
You see, this is referring to the time

00:52:33.045 --> 00:52:37.216 line:90% position:50% align:center
when Jesus comes with his holy ones.

00:52:37.216 --> 00:52:39.427 line:90% position:50% align:center
So looking at our timeline,

00:52:39.427 --> 00:52:41.470 line:90% position:50% align:center
what does it show us?

00:52:41.470 --> 00:52:46.350 line:90% position:50% align:center
That this is at the very end of the great tribulation

00:52:46.350 --> 00:52:51.272 line:90% position:50% align:center
when people are judged as being goats.

00:52:51.272 --> 00:52:56.277 line:90% position:50% align:center
Specifically,
they have been given this judgment.

00:52:56.277 --> 00:52:59.613 line:90% position:50% align:center
But there are some other questions
that come up.

00:52:59.613 --> 00:53:02.283 line:90% position:50% align:center
You see, these ones who are judged as goats

00:53:02.283 --> 00:53:04.785 line:90% position:50% align:center
(those who receive everlasting destruction)

00:53:04.785 --> 00:53:09.498 line:90% position:50% align:center
obviously have had adequate
opportunity (have had a full opportunity)

00:53:09.498 --> 00:53:12.460 line:90% position:50% align:center
to accept or reject the Kingdom.

00:53:12.460 --> 00:53:16.630 line:90% position:50% align:center
But what about those prior
to that final judgment?

00:53:16.630 --> 00:53:19.508 line:90% position:50% align:center
So the great tribulation starts.

00:53:19.508 --> 00:53:21.719 line:90% position:50% align:center
We’re not sure how long it goes,

00:53:21.719 --> 00:53:26.557 line:90% position:50% align:center
but each day it goes on,
there are people who no doubt will die.

00:53:26.557 --> 00:53:29.769 line:90% position:50% align:center
Do you realize that every day worldwide

00:53:29.769 --> 00:53:32.772 line:90% position:50% align:center
about 150,000 people die

00:53:32.772 --> 00:53:37.818 line:90% position:50% align:center
either of natural causes or wars,
sicknesses, and so on?

00:53:37.818 --> 00:53:40.571 line:90% position:50% align:center
So, what about those ones?

00:53:40.571 --> 00:53:44.825 line:90% position:50% align:center
They’re not actually killed
by Jehovah as a punishment.

00:53:44.825 --> 00:53:47.328 line:90% position:50% align:center
So, what do we need to remember?

00:53:47.328 --> 00:53:52.333 line:90% position:50% align:center
The merciful Judge knows
who should be resurrected

00:53:52.333 --> 00:53:54.418 line:90% position:50% align:center
and who shouldn’t be resurrected.

00:53:54.418 --> 00:53:59.423 line:90% position:50% align:center
So we can’t be dogmatic
about those ones who may die at that time.

00:53:59.423 --> 00:54:03.511 line:90% position:50% align:center
We know that Jehovah
and Jesus will do the right thing.

00:54:04.637 --> 00:54:08.432 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, another final interesting question:

00:54:09.475 --> 00:54:14.438 line:90% position:50% align:center
Will all those living
during the great tribulation

00:54:14.438 --> 00:54:18.526 line:90% position:50% align:center
have a full opportunity

00:54:18.526 --> 00:54:21.904 line:90% position:50% align:center
to decide either
for the Kingdom or against it?

00:54:23.114 --> 00:54:25.116 line:90% position:50% align:center
How would you answer?

00:54:25.116 --> 00:54:26.951 line:90% position:50% align:center
Don’t say it out loud.

00:54:28.327 --> 00:54:32.998 line:90% position:50% align:center
The simple answer is, we don’t know,

00:54:33.749 --> 00:54:38.087 line:90% position:50% align:center
and we don’t need to know
because we’re not the judges.

00:54:38.087 --> 00:54:40.297 line:90% position:50% align:center
It’s above our pay grade.

00:54:41.841 --> 00:54:45.261 line:90% position:50% align:center
But now, there may be a little voice
in you saying: ‘But why don’t we know?

00:54:45.261 --> 00:54:49.098 line:90% position:50% align:center
I mean, I’ve always believed
that during that time, that’s it.’

00:54:50.432 --> 00:54:53.811 line:90% position:50% align:center
But, you see, each day, as we mentioned,

00:54:53.811 --> 00:54:57.022 line:90% position:50% align:center
150,000 people on average die,

00:54:57.022 --> 00:55:02.027 line:90% position:50% align:center
but 350,000 new babies are born each day.

00:55:02.820 --> 00:55:06.615 line:90% position:50% align:center
So even if the great tribulation
was only a few days long,

00:55:06.615 --> 00:55:10.870 line:90% position:50% align:center
each day you’ve got more babies being born.

00:55:10.870 --> 00:55:14.456 line:90% position:50% align:center
And what about areas where the good news

00:55:14.456 --> 00:55:17.084 line:90% position:50% align:center
hasn’t reached to the greatest extent,

00:55:17.084 --> 00:55:20.296 line:90% position:50% align:center
maybe in lands where our work is restricted?

00:55:20.296 --> 00:55:25.301 line:90% position:50% align:center
We might be wondering, ‘Well, will we get
to preach to every individual?’

00:55:25.301 --> 00:55:28.596 line:90% position:50% align:center
Matthew 10:23, if you look at it later,

00:55:28.596 --> 00:55:31.682 line:90% position:50% align:center
seems to indicate that maybe we won’t.

00:55:31.682 --> 00:55:34.727 line:90% position:50% align:center
So, now, here’s an interesting question:

00:55:34.727 --> 00:55:39.565 line:90% position:50% align:center
Is it reasonable for us to say
that Jehovah and Jesus

00:55:39.565 --> 00:55:43.569 line:90% position:50% align:center
automatically label millions
of people as goats

00:55:43.569 --> 00:55:48.407 line:90% position:50% align:center
even though they have never
had a full opportunity to respond?

00:55:49.116 --> 00:55:51.243 line:90% position:50% align:center
Interesting question.

00:55:51.243 --> 00:55:55.873 line:90% position:50% align:center
If they haven’t had a full opportunity
and they die at that time,

00:55:55.873 --> 00:55:59.460 line:90% position:50% align:center
is it possible
that they may receive a resurrection

00:55:59.460 --> 00:56:01.754 line:90% position:50% align:center
as unrighteous persons?

00:56:01.754 --> 00:56:03.380 line:90% position:50% align:center
What’s the answer?

00:56:03.380 --> 00:56:05.925 line:90% position:50% align:center
We simply don’t know.

00:56:05.925 --> 00:56:07.927 line:90% position:50% align:center
We can’t be dogmatic,

00:56:07.927 --> 00:56:11.805 line:90% position:50% align:center
and we shouldn’t be dogmatic
because we don’t know.

00:56:13.140 --> 00:56:17.811 line:90% position:50% align:center
But, rather, let’s take comfort
in what we do know.

00:56:17.811 --> 00:56:19.647 line:90% position:50% align:center
And what do we know?

00:56:19.647 --> 00:56:23.234 line:90% position:50% align:center
We know that Jehovah and Jesus are merciful,

00:56:23.234 --> 00:56:26.153 line:90% position:50% align:center
that they will always do the right thing.

00:56:26.153 --> 00:56:29.907 line:90% position:50% align:center
At Ezekiel 33:11, what does it say?

00:56:29.907 --> 00:56:33.744 line:90% position:50% align:center
‘Jehovah takes no delight
in the death of a wicked person.’

00:56:33.744 --> 00:56:35.955 line:90% position:50% align:center
He wants them to change.

00:56:35.955 --> 00:56:40.292 line:90% position:50% align:center
And we know that Jehovah and Jesus
will judge each individual

00:56:40.292 --> 00:56:44.672 line:90% position:50% align:center
in a balanced, righteous, and merciful way.

00:56:45.506 --> 00:56:47.591 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, now, at this point, you think:

00:56:47.591 --> 00:56:50.261 line:90% position:50% align:center
‘Wow!
That’s a lot to take in.’

00:56:51.053 --> 00:56:54.265 line:90% position:50% align:center
Maybe your hand
is a little tired from taking notes.

00:56:54.265 --> 00:56:55.766 line:90% position:50% align:center
Don’t worry.

00:56:55.766 --> 00:56:57.601 line:90% position:50% align:center
An upcoming <i>Watchtower</i>

00:56:57.601 --> 00:57:02.564 line:90% position:50% align:center
is going to give us all the details on this,
so stay tuned.

00:57:02.564 --> 00:57:06.026 line:90% position:50% align:center
But in the meantime,
what do we need to keep doing?

00:57:06.026 --> 00:57:10.614 line:90% position:50% align:center
We need to keep preaching the message
to as many people as possible.

00:57:10.614 --> 00:57:14.451 line:90% position:50% align:center
We have no idea what results
may come from that.

00:57:14.451 --> 00:57:17.162 line:90% position:50% align:center
And as we keep on preaching, remember,

00:57:17.162 --> 00:57:21.208 line:90% position:50% align:center
leave the judging to Jehovah and Jesus!

00:57:21.208 --> 00:57:24.461 line:90% position:50% align:center
They will <i>always</i>  do the right thing,

00:57:24.461 --> 00:57:26.672 line:90% position:50% align:center
the merciful and just thing.

00:57:26.672 --> 00:57:30.968 line:90% position:50% align:center
Of that we can be absolutely confident!

00:57:48.193 --> 00:57:50.446 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, I was going to ask you,
Wasn’t that exciting?

