00:59:57.406 --> 00:59:58.740 line:90% position:50% align:center
OK!

01:00:05.914 --> 01:00:07.541 line:90% position:50% align:center
Hey, Zoe.

01:00:08.417 --> 01:00:10.502 line:90% position:50% align:center
Oh, hey.

01:00:10.502 --> 01:00:12.463 line:90% position:50% align:center
What ya doing?

01:00:12.463 --> 01:00:16.049 line:90% position:50% align:center
Um, I’m just about to meet . . .

01:00:16.049 --> 01:00:18.135 line:90% position:50% align:center
. . . Sophia.

01:00:18.135 --> 01:00:20.137 line:90% position:50% align:center
Why do you hang out with her?

01:00:21.763 --> 01:00:24.141 line:90% position:50% align:center
She’s so . . .

01:00:24.141 --> 01:00:25.934 line:90% position:50% align:center
Different?

01:00:26.643 --> 01:00:27.895 line:90% position:50% align:center
Weird.

01:00:32.357 --> 01:00:36.820 line:90% position:50% align:center
She never does anything fun.

01:00:37.696 --> 01:00:40.407 line:90% position:50% align:center
I mean you’re different, Zoe.

01:00:41.533 --> 01:00:43.535 line:90% position:50% align:center
But in a cool way.

01:00:44.203 --> 01:00:48.707 line:90% position:50% align:center
You should hang out with us—not that loser.

01:00:48.707 --> 01:00:52.878 line:90% position:50% align:center
Angela, please see me immediately.

01:00:53.795 --> 01:00:56.006 line:90% position:50% align:center
See ya later, Zoe.

01:01:06.808 --> 01:01:10.646 line:90% position:50% align:center
Does it bother you
that others think you’re different?

01:01:11.438 --> 01:01:12.898 line:90% position:50% align:center
What do you mean?

01:01:15.609 --> 01:01:18.570 line:90% position:50% align:center
Some of the other kids say things 

01:01:18.570 --> 01:01:22.908 line:90% position:50% align:center
like it’s weird you can’t celebrate holidays

01:01:22.908 --> 01:01:25.702 line:90% position:50% align:center
and that you can’t have fun.

01:01:28.372 --> 01:01:29.915 line:90% position:50% align:center
What?

01:01:29.915 --> 01:01:32.167 line:90% position:50% align:center
Who says we can’t have fun?

01:01:51.144 --> 01:01:53.188 line:90% position:50% align:center
Of course we can have fun.

01:01:53.689 --> 01:01:58.151 line:90% position:50% align:center
It can be hard sometimes,
but it’s good to be different,

01:01:58.151 --> 01:02:00.237 line:90% position:50% align:center
like Jesus.

01:02:00.237 --> 01:02:02.698 line:90% position:50% align:center
Like Jesus?

01:02:03.156 --> 01:02:06.994 line:90% position:50% align:center
Yeah, that’s right!
We learn a lot about him at family worship.

01:02:08.245 --> 01:02:11.164 line:90% position:50% align:center
In the Bible, Jesus said his followers

01:02:11.164 --> 01:02:13.542 line:90% position:50% align:center
would be “no part of the world.”

01:02:13.542 --> 01:02:17.212 line:90% position:50% align:center
What do you think it means
to be “no part of the world”?

01:02:18.672 --> 01:02:19.840 line:90% position:50% align:center
Hmm.

01:02:27.139 --> 01:02:28.181 line:90% position:50% align:center
Whoa!

01:02:28.181 --> 01:02:29.391 line:90% position:50% align:center
Whoa!

01:02:33.478 --> 01:02:38.525 line:90% position:50% align:center
T-minus ten, nine, eight, seven,

01:02:38.525 --> 01:02:42.279 line:90% position:50% align:center
six, five, four,

01:02:42.279 --> 01:02:45.616 line:90% position:50% align:center
three, two, one.

01:02:45.616 --> 01:02:49.369 line:90% position:50% align:center
We have liftoff!

01:03:02.633 --> 01:03:05.135 line:90% position:50% align:center
That’s a good guess.

01:03:05.135 --> 01:03:07.679 line:90% position:50% align:center
But we don’t have to leave the planet.

01:03:09.014 --> 01:03:11.600 line:90% position:50% align:center
He said that he did not want
to take his followers

01:03:11.600 --> 01:03:13.977 line:90% position:50% align:center
“out of the world” but . . .

01:03:14.394 --> 01:03:16.772 line:90% position:50% align:center
. . . that they should be
“no part of the world”!

01:03:17.356 --> 01:03:19.358 line:90% position:50% align:center
That’s right, honey.

01:03:20.317 --> 01:03:22.527 line:90% position:50% align:center
What else did Jesus say?

01:03:24.780 --> 01:03:27.324 line:90% position:50% align:center
“They are no part of the world,

01:03:27.324 --> 01:03:30.118 line:90% position:50% align:center
just as I am no part of the world.”

01:03:31.203 --> 01:03:34.247 line:90% position:50% align:center
How was Jesus “no part of the world”?

01:03:35.207 --> 01:03:36.583 line:90% position:50% align:center
Let’s see!

01:03:37.292 --> 01:03:40.379 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jesus was different from everyone else,

01:03:40.379 --> 01:03:42.589 line:90% position:50% align:center
and so were his friends.

01:03:42.589 --> 01:03:44.216 line:10% position:50% align:center
He showed others

01:03:44.216 --> 01:03:46.468 line:10% position:50% align:center
how to be different in what they did,

01:03:47.344 --> 01:03:50.972 line:90% position:50% align:center
what they said, and even how they thought.

01:03:52.307 --> 01:03:54.017 line:90% position:50% align:center
Really?
How?

01:03:55.018 --> 01:03:58.647 line:90% position:50% align:center
People aren’t always nice
to others they think are different.

01:04:00.524 --> 01:04:02.693 line:90% position:50% align:center
But Jesus wanted to help everyone.

01:04:02.693 --> 01:04:06.697 line:90% position:50% align:center
And that made some people very angry.

01:04:06.697 --> 01:04:09.533 line:90% position:50% align:center
They wanted Jesus to be more like them.

01:04:10.409 --> 01:04:13.120 line:90% position:50% align:center
But he didn’t worry about what they thought,

01:04:13.120 --> 01:04:16.623 line:90% position:50% align:center
because whom did Jesus want to be like?

01:04:16.623 --> 01:04:18.166 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehovah!

01:04:18.166 --> 01:04:20.168 line:90% position:50% align:center
That’s right.

01:04:20.168 --> 01:04:22.212 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehovah said that those who obeyed his voice

01:04:22.212 --> 01:04:24.464 line:90% position:50% align:center
were special to him.

01:04:24.464 --> 01:04:27.259 line:90% position:50% align:center
So when you love and obey Jehovah

01:04:27.259 --> 01:04:30.053 line:90% position:50% align:center
and you are “no part of the world”
like Jesus, . . .

01:04:30.971 --> 01:04:32.973 line:90% position:50% align:center
. . . that makes you special to Him!

01:04:36.268 --> 01:04:38.520 line:90% position:50% align:center
I don’t know if I could ever be like you.

01:04:43.525 --> 01:04:45.277 line:90% position:50% align:center
What do you mean?

01:04:46.778 --> 01:04:49.448 line:90% position:50% align:center
OK, OK, settle down.

01:04:53.952 --> 01:04:58.081 line:90% position:50% align:center
I don’t know.
I-I gotta go.

01:05:28.028 --> 01:05:31.865 line:90% position:50% align:center
When you love and obey Jehovah,
that makes you special to him!

01:06:05.065 --> 01:06:06.191 line:90% position:50% align:center
Hey!

01:06:06.191 --> 01:06:07.609 line:90% position:50% align:center
It’s a leper!

01:06:22.958 --> 01:06:24.459 line:90% position:50% align:center
Get away!

01:06:24.459 --> 01:06:26.378 line:90% position:50% align:center
We don’t want you here!

01:07:06.042 --> 01:07:08.086 line:90% position:50% align:center
What is he doing?

01:07:08.086 --> 01:07:10.088 line:90% position:50% align:center
He shouldn’t be here!

01:07:10.463 --> 01:07:12.173 line:90% position:50% align:center
Lord,

01:07:12.173 --> 01:07:15.135 line:90% position:50% align:center
if you just want to,

01:07:15.135 --> 01:07:17.637 line:90% position:50% align:center
you can make me clean.

01:07:23.894 --> 01:07:25.478 line:90% position:50% align:center
I want to!

01:07:27.647 --> 01:07:29.190 line:90% position:50% align:center
Be made clean.

01:07:31.776 --> 01:07:33.486 line:90% position:50% align:center
It’s a miracle!

01:07:41.328 --> 01:07:43.455 line:90% position:50% align:center
Can you believe this?

01:07:43.455 --> 01:07:45.332 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jesus isn’t one of us.

01:07:51.379 --> 01:07:53.173 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jesus was different

01:07:53.173 --> 01:07:55.634 line:90% position:50% align:center
in what he did, said, and thought.

01:08:00.305 --> 01:08:01.973 line:90% position:50% align:center
I’m sorry about your grandma.

01:08:01.973 --> 01:08:03.600 line:90% position:50% align:center
This is for you.

01:08:03.600 --> 01:08:05.477 line:90% position:50% align:center
It will help you feel better.

01:08:05.477 --> 01:08:06.728 line:90% position:50% align:center
Thank you.

01:08:07.270 --> 01:08:10.523 line:90% position:50% align:center
And that made some people very angry.

01:08:11.274 --> 01:08:12.275 line:90% position:50% align:center
Uhhh!

01:08:17.656 --> 01:08:19.783 line:90% position:50% align:center
Oops, I didn’t see you there.

01:08:20.784 --> 01:08:22.786 line:90% position:50% align:center
Are you OK?

01:08:23.703 --> 01:08:25.705 line:90% position:50% align:center
Let me help.

01:08:27.207 --> 01:08:29.501 line:90% position:50% align:center
Sometimes they pick on me too.

01:08:31.252 --> 01:08:35.006 line:90% position:50% align:center
People aren’t always nice to others
whom they think are different.

01:08:35.548 --> 01:08:39.386 line:90% position:50% align:center
You should hang out with us—not that loser.

01:08:40.971 --> 01:08:44.099 line:90% position:50% align:center
But Jesus wanted to be
like his Father, Jehovah,

01:08:44.599 --> 01:08:47.268 line:90% position:50% align:center
and that’s what made him special.

01:08:49.813 --> 01:08:51.940 line:90% position:50% align:center
Hey, darling, how was your study with Sophia?

01:08:52.774 --> 01:08:56.277 line:90% position:50% align:center
Mom, there’s something I want to show you.

01:08:56.277 --> 01:08:58.029 line:90% position:50% align:center
Oh, OK.

01:09:06.454 --> 01:09:08.456 line:90% position:50% align:center
All right, everyone,

01:09:08.456 --> 01:09:10.041 line:90% position:50% align:center
enjoy the holiday party!

01:09:15.213 --> 01:09:16.548 line:90% position:50% align:center
Hey, Zoe,

01:09:16.548 --> 01:09:19.300 line:90% position:50% align:center
aren’t you coming?

01:09:28.101 --> 01:09:30.311 line:90% position:50% align:center
Let me show you how it’s done.

01:09:32.814 --> 01:09:34.190 line:90% position:50% align:center
Hi, guys!

01:09:34.774 --> 01:09:36.651 line:90% position:50% align:center
You didn’t go to the party?

01:09:37.402 --> 01:09:39.988 line:90% position:50% align:center
No.
I want to do the right thing.

01:09:42.615 --> 01:09:45.702 line:90% position:50% align:center
OK.
Let’s have some fun!

01:09:48.496 --> 01:09:51.041 line:90% position:50% align:center
Ugh.
Not again!

01:10:08.308 --> 01:10:12.687 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, we certainly cherish
these beautiful videos, don’t we?

01:10:12.687 --> 01:10:14.689 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, with that in mind,

01:10:14.689 --> 01:10:18.526 line:90% position:50% align:center
would you like to know
what is happening at the Ramapo site

01:10:18.526 --> 01:10:22.781 line:90% position:50% align:center
as well as
the video production in Australasia?

01:10:22.781 --> 01:10:23.990 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, you’ll enjoy this.

01:10:23.990 --> 01:10:26.201 line:90% position:50% align:center
Let’s give our attention to Brother Lett

01:10:26.201 --> 01:10:28.745 line:90% position:50% align:center
as he provides an update for us

01:10:28.745 --> 01:10:33.083 line:90% position:50% align:center
in his part that is titled
“Jehovah’s Chariot Is on the Move.”

01:10:34.834 --> 01:10:37.295 line:90% position:50% align:center
I’m glad you indicated you want to hear this.

01:10:41.257 --> 01:10:45.720 line:90% position:50% align:center
Second Samuel 15:1

01:10:45.720 --> 01:10:49.390 line:90% position:50% align:center
tells us that Absalom,

01:10:49.390 --> 01:10:52.602 line:90% position:50% align:center
who was trying to usurp the throne,

01:10:52.602 --> 01:10:56.189 line:90% position:50% align:center
had a royal chariot built for himself.

01:10:56.189 --> 01:10:59.150 line:90% position:50% align:center
It was pulled by majestic horses.

01:10:59.150 --> 01:11:02.654 line:90% position:50% align:center
Fifty men ran ahead of that chariot.

01:11:02.654 --> 01:11:04.823 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, as impressive

01:11:04.823 --> 01:11:08.993 line:90% position:50% align:center
as that chariot and rider
may have seemed to many,

01:11:08.993 --> 01:11:12.330 line:90% position:50% align:center
compared to the celestial chariot

01:11:12.330 --> 01:11:14.666 line:90% position:50% align:center
mentioned in Ezekiel chapter 1,

01:11:14.666 --> 01:11:18.253 line:90% position:50% align:center
Absalom’s chariot would be a sluggish,

01:11:18.253 --> 01:11:20.755 line:90% position:50% align:center
minuscule rattletrap.

01:11:22.632 --> 01:11:27.637 line:90% position:50% align:center
As we know, that chariot
mentioned in Ezekiel chapter 1

01:11:27.637 --> 01:11:30.473 line:90% position:50% align:center
represents the heavenly part

01:11:30.473 --> 01:11:32.809 line:90% position:50% align:center
of Jehovah’s organization.

01:11:32.809 --> 01:11:35.395 line:90% position:50% align:center
Who is the rider of this chariot?

01:11:35.395 --> 01:11:37.397 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehovah himself.

01:11:37.397 --> 01:11:39.858 line:90% position:50% align:center
Why is he depicted this way?

01:11:39.858 --> 01:11:42.193 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, Jehovah lovingly controls

01:11:42.193 --> 01:11:45.446 line:90% position:50% align:center
the movements of his organization

01:11:45.446 --> 01:11:48.908 line:90% position:50% align:center
to accomplish his will and purpose.

01:11:48.908 --> 01:11:52.412 line:90% position:50% align:center
No wonder Ezekiel 1:18

01:11:52.412 --> 01:11:56.833 line:90% position:50% align:center
describes the rims
of the wheels of the chariot

01:11:56.833 --> 01:11:59.294 line:90% position:50% align:center
as having “eyes all around”!

01:11:59.294 --> 01:12:03.715 line:90% position:50% align:center
All-seeing Jehovah directs everything.

01:12:04.424 --> 01:12:07.051 line:90% position:50% align:center
What is the speed of Jehovah’s chariot?

01:12:07.969 --> 01:12:10.763 line:90% position:50% align:center
Absalom’s chariot may have been able
to reach speeds

01:12:10.763 --> 01:12:13.349 line:90% position:50% align:center
of up to 45 miles an hour (72 km/hr)

01:12:13.349 --> 01:12:15.351 line:90% position:50% align:center
—the speed of a racehorse.

01:12:15.351 --> 01:12:17.604 line:90% position:50% align:center
But what about Jehovah’s chariot?

01:12:17.604 --> 01:12:22.525 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, in the Bible in verse 14 of chapter 1,

01:12:22.525 --> 01:12:25.361 line:90% position:50% align:center
it describes its movements

01:12:25.361 --> 01:12:29.908 line:90% position:50% align:center
in comparison with “flashes of lightning.”

01:12:30.617 --> 01:12:32.994 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, a flash of lightning

01:12:32.994 --> 01:12:35.788 line:90% position:50% align:center
travels at 186,000 miles per second
(300,000 km/sec),

01:12:35.788 --> 01:12:37.373 line:90% position:50% align:center
the speed of light.

01:12:37.373 --> 01:12:40.835 line:90% position:50% align:center
But if we think about it,
Jehovah’s chariot is a lot faster than that.

01:12:40.835 --> 01:12:42.962 line:90% position:50% align:center
In fact, we could say

01:12:42.962 --> 01:12:46.049 line:90% position:50% align:center
it travels at the speed of thought,

01:12:46.049 --> 01:12:48.927 line:90% position:50% align:center
at the speed of Jehovah’s thought.

01:12:48.927 --> 01:12:53.348 line:90% position:50% align:center
And obviously
that would be immeasurably fast.

01:12:53.348 --> 01:12:57.060 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, we can’t see into the invisible realm

01:12:57.060 --> 01:13:01.439 line:90% position:50% align:center
and see how Jehovah is using
the heavenly part of his organization

01:13:01.439 --> 01:13:04.943 line:90% position:50% align:center
with lightning speed
to accomplish his will and purpose,

01:13:04.943 --> 01:13:08.613 line:90% position:50% align:center
but we can see how fast things are moving

01:13:08.613 --> 01:13:12.784 line:90% position:50% align:center
in the visible part
of Jehovah’s organization.

01:13:12.784 --> 01:13:14.619 line:90% position:50% align:center
And that only makes sense
—doesn’t it?—

01:13:14.619 --> 01:13:19.249 line:90% position:50% align:center
because the earthly part
is closely related to the heavenly

01:13:19.249 --> 01:13:21.417 line:90% position:50% align:center
and is actually a reflection

01:13:21.417 --> 01:13:25.088 line:90% position:50% align:center
of the heavenly part
of Jehovah’s organization.

01:13:25.088 --> 01:13:27.632 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, the foregoing discussion

01:13:27.632 --> 01:13:31.094 line:90% position:50% align:center
brings us to what Brother Cook mentioned

01:13:31.094 --> 01:13:36.057 line:90% position:50% align:center
are updates of two fast-moving projects

01:13:36.057 --> 01:13:39.227 line:90% position:50% align:center
that Jehovah obviously is directing,

01:13:39.227 --> 01:13:42.522 line:90% position:50% align:center
and we’re going to get brought up to speed.

01:13:42.522 --> 01:13:44.357 line:90% position:50% align:center
You like the way I used that
—right?—

01:13:44.357 --> 01:13:49.153 line:90% position:50% align:center
up to speed,
since we’re talking about moving.

01:13:49.153 --> 01:13:51.155 line:90% position:50% align:center
But things are happening,

01:13:51.155 --> 01:13:54.826 line:90% position:50% align:center
and Jehovah certainly is directing matters.

01:13:54.826 --> 01:13:56.411 line:90% position:50% align:center
And, as mentioned,

01:13:56.411 --> 01:14:00.581 line:90% position:50% align:center
we’re going to have an update
regarding the audio/video facility

01:14:00.581 --> 01:14:04.210 line:90% position:50% align:center
being built at Ramapo, New York.

01:14:04.210 --> 01:14:08.214 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, you’ll probably recall

01:14:08.214 --> 01:14:12.885 line:90% position:50% align:center
that it’s being built on property
that the organization already owned.

01:14:12.885 --> 01:14:16.264 line:90% position:50% align:center
And it’s conveniently located
only two miles (3 km)

01:14:16.264 --> 01:14:20.810 line:90% position:50% align:center
from our world headquarters facility
at Warwick.

01:14:20.810 --> 01:14:23.730 line:90% position:50% align:center
And a very interesting side point is

01:14:23.730 --> 01:14:26.899 line:90% position:50% align:center
the Governing Body tried for several years
(really hard)

01:14:26.899 --> 01:14:29.277 line:90% position:50% align:center
to sell this property

01:14:29.277 --> 01:14:32.196 line:90% position:50% align:center
with absolutely no results.

01:14:33.281 --> 01:14:36.034 line:90% position:50% align:center
Then we came to realize

01:14:36.034 --> 01:14:38.494 line:90% position:50% align:center
that this is ideal property

01:14:38.494 --> 01:14:41.748 line:90% position:50% align:center
to build a much-needed facility

01:14:41.748 --> 01:14:44.834 line:90% position:50% align:center
that can consolidate onto one site

01:14:44.834 --> 01:14:48.796 line:90% position:50% align:center
the functions currently being done
on many different properties

01:14:48.796 --> 01:14:50.923 line:90% position:50% align:center
—one site to produce

01:14:50.923 --> 01:14:55.595 line:90% position:50% align:center
our audio/video and beautiful artwork.

01:14:55.595 --> 01:14:59.932 line:90% position:50% align:center
So this is just another example
of Jehovah’s eyes seeing things.

01:14:59.932 --> 01:15:04.437 line:90% position:50% align:center
In fact, we think of his words in Psalm 32.

01:15:04.437 --> 01:15:09.025 line:90% position:50% align:center
Please go there—Psalm 32:8.

01:15:09.025 --> 01:15:13.780 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehovah says: “I will give you insight

01:15:13.780 --> 01:15:17.200 line:90% position:50% align:center
“and instruct you in the way you should go.

01:15:17.200 --> 01:15:19.577 line:90% position:50% align:center
“I will give you advice

01:15:19.577 --> 01:15:22.622 line:90% position:50% align:center
with my eye upon you.”

01:15:22.622 --> 01:15:26.042 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehovah is obviously
lovingly directing things.

01:15:26.042 --> 01:15:28.336 line:90% position:50% align:center
But I’m sure you’d like to see this video now

01:15:28.336 --> 01:15:30.338 line:90% position:50% align:center
that will give you an update

01:15:30.338 --> 01:15:34.050 line:90% position:50% align:center
on what is happening there at Ramapo.

01:15:34.050 --> 01:15:36.052 line:90% position:50% align:center
So enjoy the video.

01:15:38.888 --> 01:15:41.766 line:10% position:50% align:center
The specific purpose of the Ramapo project

01:15:41.766 --> 01:15:44.644 line:10% position:50% align:center
is to bring all media facilities

01:15:44.644 --> 01:15:46.687 line:90% position:50% align:center
under one roof.

01:15:47.897 --> 01:15:51.109 line:90% position:50% align:center
As a project begins,
we always want things to move fast.

01:15:51.109 --> 01:15:52.860 line:10% position:50% align:center
But sometimes the reality is

01:15:52.860 --> 01:15:53.945 line:10% position:50% align:center
that it doesn’t happen as fast

01:15:53.945 --> 01:15:55.029 line:10% position:50% align:center
as we would like it to.

01:15:55.029 --> 01:15:57.365 line:10% position:50% align:center
It’s been several years

01:15:57.365 --> 01:15:59.409 line:10% position:50% align:center
of some pretty dynamic planning,

01:15:59.409 --> 01:16:01.452 line:10% position:50% align:center
and we’ve seen a lot of twists and turns

01:16:01.452 --> 01:16:02.912 line:90% position:50% align:center
and changes along the way.

01:16:02.912 --> 01:16:04.539 line:10% position:50% align:center
We’ve had a number of challenges

01:16:04.539 --> 01:16:05.873 line:10% position:50% align:center
on the Ramapo project.

01:16:07.917 --> 01:16:09.919 line:90% position:50% align:center
In the state of New York,

01:16:09.919 --> 01:16:13.631 line:90% position:50% align:center
there’s only a certain season
when you can take trees down.

01:16:13.631 --> 01:16:15.758 line:10% position:50% align:center
We’re only allowed to remove trees

01:16:15.758 --> 01:16:19.429 line:10% position:50% align:center
between November and the end of March.

01:16:19.429 --> 01:16:24.016 line:90% position:50% align:center
The town board approved the special permit
for us to be able to cut the trees.

01:16:24.016 --> 01:16:26.978 line:90% position:50% align:center
However,
when we went to exercise that permit,

01:16:26.978 --> 01:16:29.063 line:90% position:50% align:center
we realized that another agency

01:16:29.063 --> 01:16:33.317 line:90% position:50% align:center
still had to give their permission
for us to be able to use it,

01:16:33.317 --> 01:16:34.819 line:90% position:50% align:center
which we didn’t get.

01:16:34.819 --> 01:16:36.696 line:10% position:50% align:center
Originally we had planned

01:16:36.696 --> 01:16:39.490 line:10% position:50% align:center
about 12 weeks to do all of this work.

01:16:39.490 --> 01:16:42.910 line:90% position:50% align:center
And that 12 weeks
included using mechanized equipment.

01:16:42.910 --> 01:16:45.997 line:90% position:50% align:center
If that wasn’t accomplished,
we would be waiting an entire year

01:16:45.997 --> 01:16:47.999 line:90% position:50% align:center
to be able to cut those trees.

01:16:47.999 --> 01:16:51.419 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, the window started closing
from 12 weeks to 8 weeks

01:16:51.419 --> 01:16:53.421 line:90% position:50% align:center
all the way down to 6 weeks.

01:16:53.421 --> 01:16:57.091 line:90% position:50% align:center
And then somehow,
something in the permitting language

01:16:57.091 --> 01:17:00.052 line:90% position:50% align:center
opened our eyes to a new possibility

01:17:00.052 --> 01:17:03.556 line:90% position:50% align:center
that allowed us to take the trees down
in a different way.

01:17:03.556 --> 01:17:05.933 line:90% position:50% align:center
We got permission to cut the trees,

01:17:05.933 --> 01:17:08.352 line:90% position:50% align:center
but we had to cut the trees all by hand.

01:17:09.562 --> 01:17:10.813 line:90% position:50% align:center
And in four weeks,

01:17:10.813 --> 01:17:12.565 line:90% position:50% align:center
we used an outside contractor

01:17:12.565 --> 01:17:14.942 line:90% position:50% align:center
to take down all the trees
that we needed . . .

01:17:15.776 --> 01:17:18.863 line:90% position:50% align:center
. . . two weeks early
of the end of the tree-cutting season.

01:17:20.573 --> 01:17:23.743 line:90% position:50% align:center
Every single day
there’s still much work to be done

01:17:23.743 --> 01:17:25.703 line:90% position:50% align:center
to get us the needed permits.

01:17:25.703 --> 01:17:27.330 line:90% position:50% align:center
The design is continuing,

01:17:27.330 --> 01:17:29.582 line:90% position:50% align:center
and the estimating for the project
is continuing.

01:17:29.582 --> 01:17:30.750 line:90% position:50% align:center
That hasn’t stopped.

01:17:30.750 --> 01:17:32.793 line:90% position:50% align:center
That hasn’t slowed up one bit.

01:17:33.628 --> 01:17:36.464 line:90% position:50% align:center
Because of some of the delays
that we experienced,

01:17:36.464 --> 01:17:39.759 line:90% position:50% align:center
there was a need to reassign
some of our brothers and sisters

01:17:39.759 --> 01:17:41.219 line:90% position:50% align:center
within the organization.

01:17:41.219 --> 01:17:42.887 line:90% position:50% align:center
We had these willing volunteers.

01:17:42.887 --> 01:17:46.432 line:90% position:50% align:center
They were skilled; they were trained;
they were willing to do whatever was needed,

01:17:46.432 --> 01:17:49.227 line:90% position:50% align:center
but we just didn’t have
the work for them at the time.

01:17:51.854 --> 01:17:54.357 line:90% position:50% align:center
We were able to communicate
with different departments

01:17:54.357 --> 01:17:56.859 line:90% position:50% align:center
in the branch and at headquarters.

01:17:57.568 --> 01:18:00.696 line:90% position:50% align:center
And it just so happened
that many of these departments

01:18:00.696 --> 01:18:03.032 line:90% position:50% align:center
had been praying for additional help.

01:18:03.866 --> 01:18:05.910 line:90% position:50% align:center
The brothers had a meeting with us,
and they said:

01:18:05.910 --> 01:18:09.539 line:90% position:50% align:center
“We know you’re not 100 percent busy
like you want to be.

01:18:09.539 --> 01:18:12.458 line:90% position:50% align:center
“We’ll be giving a number of you
new assignments.

01:18:13.251 --> 01:18:15.461 line:10% position:50% align:center
“Most of you will go out for a while

01:18:15.461 --> 01:18:17.547 line:10% position:50% align:center
while we get our permits and come back.”

01:18:17.547 --> 01:18:19.715 line:90% position:50% align:center
They said that I would be going into CDE,

01:18:19.715 --> 01:18:22.927 line:90% position:50% align:center
and I didn’t even know what that was:
Computer Department Engineering.

01:18:22.927 --> 01:18:24.971 line:90% position:50% align:center
And I thought:
‘That’s way above me.

01:18:24.971 --> 01:18:26.597 line:90% position:50% align:center
I’m a construction girl.’

01:18:26.597 --> 01:18:28.683 line:90% position:50% align:center
But actually, I’ve loved it.

01:18:28.683 --> 01:18:29.934 line:90% position:50% align:center
I’ve learned so much.

01:18:30.434 --> 01:18:31.936 line:90% position:50% align:center
And the team that I’ve worked with,

01:18:31.936 --> 01:18:35.189 line:90% position:50% align:center
I’ve gotten close to them,
and it’s been a wonderful change.

01:18:35.189 --> 01:18:38.192 line:90% position:50% align:center
It’s really shown us that Jehovah
is going to take care of us.

01:18:38.192 --> 01:18:40.778 line:90% position:50% align:center
For us to be at Ramapo

01:18:40.778 --> 01:18:44.323 line:90% position:50% align:center
was one of the most amazing privileges
we’ve ever had.

01:18:44.323 --> 01:18:46.826 line:90% position:50% align:center
But we’re still working for Jehovah

01:18:46.826 --> 01:18:49.495 line:90% position:50% align:center
and right in the center of his organization.

01:18:49.495 --> 01:18:52.748 line:90% position:50% align:center
These brothers and sisters
are real men and women of faith,

01:18:52.748 --> 01:18:56.377 line:90% position:50% align:center
helping to advance Kingdom interests
in all these other areas.

01:18:56.377 --> 01:19:00.298 line:90% position:50% align:center
Obviously, when we hit some of these points
where maybe we were waiting on approvals,

01:19:00.298 --> 01:19:01.924 line:90% position:50% align:center
the work did not stop.

01:19:01.924 --> 01:19:05.636 line:90% position:50% align:center
The time has allowed us
to work with the Bethel departments,

01:19:05.636 --> 01:19:08.639 line:90% position:50% align:center
to work with the Governing Body committees,

01:19:08.639 --> 01:19:13.603 line:90% position:50% align:center
to work with our outside
expert audio/video design teams.

01:19:13.603 --> 01:19:18.441 line:90% position:50% align:center
And so because of that,
the buildings themselves have changed.

01:19:18.441 --> 01:19:22.111 line:90% position:50% align:center
It was looked into.
How could flexible spaces be created?

01:19:22.111 --> 01:19:24.572 line:90% position:50% align:center
And also how
could some of these spaces be shared

01:19:24.572 --> 01:19:26.198 line:90% position:50% align:center
maybe between different departments

01:19:26.198 --> 01:19:28.034 line:90% position:50% align:center
to make the best use
of the property that we have?

01:19:28.868 --> 01:19:31.037 line:90% position:50% align:center
The Art Department
will be in the same building

01:19:31.037 --> 01:19:32.955 line:10% position:50% align:center
with the other aspects of media

01:19:32.955 --> 01:19:35.374 line:10% position:50% align:center
—the audio part and the video part—

01:19:35.374 --> 01:19:37.251 line:10% position:50% align:center
so that when we need to collaborate,

01:19:37.251 --> 01:19:40.254 line:90% position:50% align:center
it will be much easier to work together

01:19:40.254 --> 01:19:42.965 line:90% position:50% align:center
and we can make
the very best possible product.

01:19:44.008 --> 01:19:48.137 line:90% position:50% align:center
It’s a state-of-the-art audio/video
and art production facility.

01:19:48.137 --> 01:19:51.766 line:90% position:50% align:center
The process of designing that
and getting it to stay ahead

01:19:51.766 --> 01:19:54.935 line:90% position:50% align:center
of not only the ever-changing technologies
that we see in the industry

01:19:55.978 --> 01:19:58.356 line:10% position:50% align:center
but also the needs for the organization

01:19:58.356 --> 01:20:00.566 line:10% position:50% align:center
is a dynamic process.

01:20:00.566 --> 01:20:02.443 line:10% position:50% align:center
The facility has been designed

01:20:02.443 --> 01:20:04.570 line:10% position:50% align:center
and will be constructed in such a way

01:20:04.570 --> 01:20:07.114 line:90% position:50% align:center
that if modifications need to be made later

01:20:07.114 --> 01:20:09.158 line:90% position:50% align:center
to keep up with technology,

01:20:09.158 --> 01:20:11.452 line:90% position:50% align:center
we won’t have to deconstruct the building

01:20:11.452 --> 01:20:13.704 line:90% position:50% align:center
in order to implement those changes.

01:20:14.789 --> 01:20:16.957 line:90% position:50% align:center
We’ve developed beautiful studios

01:20:16.957 --> 01:20:19.168 line:90% position:50% align:center
that will be functional not only now

01:20:19.168 --> 01:20:21.212 line:90% position:50% align:center
but also for future projects.

01:20:22.004 --> 01:20:24.215 line:90% position:50% align:center
One exciting feature of the media center

01:20:24.215 --> 01:20:27.885 line:90% position:50% align:center
will be the use of video walls
for virtual production.

01:20:27.885 --> 01:20:32.598 line:90% position:50% align:center
In fact, we’ve already begun filming
with this new technology here at Patterson.

01:20:32.598 --> 01:20:34.225 line:90% position:50% align:center
With these video walls,

01:20:34.934 --> 01:20:37.812 line:10% position:50% align:center
we can create digital backgrounds

01:20:37.812 --> 01:20:40.147 line:10% position:50% align:center
that can be used to give the appearance

01:20:40.147 --> 01:20:43.234 line:90% position:50% align:center
that we are shooting it
in a foreign location.

01:20:43.984 --> 01:20:47.446 line:90% position:50% align:center
The Governing Body
made it very clear that their focus

01:20:47.446 --> 01:20:49.407 line:10% position:50% align:center
was the spirituality of those

01:20:49.407 --> 01:20:51.200 line:10% position:50% align:center
who are involved in our productions.

01:20:51.200 --> 01:20:55.079 line:90% position:50% align:center
If the friends have to be off-site
for long periods of time filming,

01:20:55.079 --> 01:20:57.873 line:90% position:50% align:center
it can really disrupt
their spiritual routine.

01:20:57.873 --> 01:21:01.502 line:90% position:50% align:center
Virtual production will allow us
to reduce the need to travel

01:21:01.502 --> 01:21:03.379 line:90% position:50% align:center
or to even work hours

01:21:03.379 --> 01:21:05.673 line:90% position:50% align:center
that could interfere
with spiritual activities.

01:21:06.298 --> 01:21:08.843 line:90% position:50% align:center
There are some circumstances that arise

01:21:08.843 --> 01:21:12.888 line:90% position:50% align:center
that can sometimes limit our ability
to travel to another location.

01:21:12.888 --> 01:21:15.683 line:90% position:50% align:center
But with the use of the video wall,
we won’t be stopped.

01:21:15.683 --> 01:21:18.811 line:90% position:50% align:center
Video production will continue in the studio.

01:21:18.811 --> 01:21:21.856 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now we’ll be able
to custom-make some backgrounds

01:21:21.856 --> 01:21:24.859 line:90% position:50% align:center
that actually look like Bible lands.

01:21:43.878 --> 01:21:48.174 line:90% position:50% align:center
And we’re very confident
that with Jehovah’s blessing,

01:21:48.174 --> 01:21:51.969 line:90% position:50% align:center
this new state-of-the-art facility

01:21:51.969 --> 01:21:56.599 line:90% position:50% align:center
will result in tremendous
savings and efficiency

01:21:56.599 --> 01:21:59.185 line:90% position:50% align:center
as we continue to produce

01:21:59.185 --> 01:22:01.771 line:90% position:50% align:center
beautiful videos and artwork

01:22:01.771 --> 01:22:04.106 line:90% position:50% align:center
to the benefit of the brotherhood.

01:22:04.106 --> 01:22:07.651 line:90% position:50% align:center
But now, that video you saw

01:22:07.651 --> 01:22:11.030 line:90% position:50% align:center
was actually a while back, a little time ago.

01:22:11.030 --> 01:22:14.492 line:90% position:50% align:center
We have some late-breaking news events

01:22:14.492 --> 01:22:16.869 line:90% position:50% align:center
to share with you since then.

01:22:16.869 --> 01:22:20.539 line:90% position:50% align:center
When you saw in the video the trees cut down,

01:22:20.539 --> 01:22:23.375 line:90% position:50% align:center
they were just lying haphazardly
—weren’t they?—

01:22:23.375 --> 01:22:25.461 line:90% position:50% align:center
with snow on the top.

01:22:25.461 --> 01:22:27.463 line:90% position:50% align:center
But since then,

01:22:27.463 --> 01:22:29.840 line:90% position:50% align:center
contractors have been very busy

01:22:29.840 --> 01:22:33.010 line:90% position:50% align:center
removing the trees, taking them out,

01:22:33.010 --> 01:22:35.805 line:90% position:50% align:center
and clearing the site in preparation

01:22:35.805 --> 01:22:39.141 line:90% position:50% align:center
for other work that will come.

01:22:39.141 --> 01:22:43.687 line:90% position:50% align:center
And all of this is preceding
this huge construction project

01:22:43.687 --> 01:22:45.940 line:90% position:50% align:center
that is looming just ahead.

01:22:45.940 --> 01:22:48.150 line:90% position:50% align:center
So we captured some of that work,

01:22:48.150 --> 01:22:51.612 line:90% position:50% align:center
and we also are bringing you up-to-date

01:22:51.612 --> 01:22:54.114 line:90% position:50% align:center
with a flyover video clip.

01:22:54.114 --> 01:22:55.908 line:90% position:50% align:center
So we want to show you this now

01:22:55.908 --> 01:22:57.910 line:90% position:50% align:center
so that it’ll bring you
even further up-to-date

01:22:57.910 --> 01:22:59.912 line:90% position:50% align:center
as to how things are looking.

01:23:57.344 --> 01:24:00.598 line:90% position:50% align:center
So you saw the trees being removed;

01:24:00.598 --> 01:24:04.560 line:90% position:50% align:center
you saw them carving out
the entrance there in the hillside.

01:24:04.560 --> 01:24:07.479 line:90% position:50% align:center
So a lot of exciting things are happening.

01:24:07.479 --> 01:24:11.567 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, soon contractors
are going to begin blasting away

01:24:11.567 --> 01:24:15.070 line:90% position:50% align:center
large underground rock formations

01:24:15.070 --> 01:24:17.615 line:90% position:50% align:center
to prepare the site for further site work.

01:24:17.615 --> 01:24:21.035 line:90% position:50% align:center
And according to our current time schedule

01:24:21.035 --> 01:24:23.454 line:90% position:50% align:center
—and I think
you’ll be interested to know this—

01:24:23.454 --> 01:24:27.625 line:90% position:50% align:center
in the late summer of 2024

01:24:27.625 --> 01:24:29.627 line:90% position:50% align:center
(just a few months from now),

01:24:29.627 --> 01:24:32.922 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehovah willing, with Jehovah’s blessing,

01:24:32.922 --> 01:24:36.634 line:90% position:50% align:center
we’re going to call in many more volunteers

01:24:36.634 --> 01:24:41.513 line:90% position:50% align:center
to help us
to move this project forward speedily.

01:24:41.513 --> 01:24:43.140 line:90% position:50% align:center
But dear brothers and sisters,

01:24:43.140 --> 01:24:46.060 line:90% position:50% align:center
please remember to pray

01:24:46.060 --> 01:24:49.939 line:90% position:50% align:center
 for Jehovah’s blessing on these efforts.

01:24:49.939 --> 01:24:52.441 line:90% position:50% align:center
But now, as we said, we have another update,

01:24:52.441 --> 01:24:55.903 line:90% position:50% align:center
and that’s concerning the exciting project

01:24:55.903 --> 01:24:58.447 line:90% position:50% align:center
that is going on in Australia.

01:24:58.447 --> 01:25:02.159 line:90% position:50% align:center
As you know,
it’s the series of dramas entitled

01:25:02.159 --> 01:25:05.788 line:90% position:50% align:center
<i>The Good News According to Jesus.</i>

01:25:05.788 --> 01:25:09.124 line:90% position:50% align:center
Please enjoy this video update.

01:25:12.670 --> 01:25:14.713 line:10% position:50% align:center
Now we’ll be able to custom-make

01:25:14.713 --> 01:25:17.091 line:10% position:50% align:center
some backgrounds that actually look

01:25:17.091 --> 01:25:18.759 line:90% position:50% align:center
like Bible lands.

01:25:18.759 --> 01:25:21.345 line:90% position:50% align:center
And so <i>The Good News According to Jesus</i>  project

01:25:21.345 --> 01:25:24.848 line:90% position:50% align:center
is the perfect candidate
for the use of virtual production.

01:25:25.808 --> 01:25:28.560 line:90% position:50% align:center
A video wall will be installed
and ready for use

01:25:28.560 --> 01:25:31.772 line:90% position:50% align:center
at the Australasia branch in early 2024.

01:25:39.279 --> 01:25:41.323 line:90% position:50% align:center
There are many formats out there in the world

01:25:41.323 --> 01:25:43.826 line:90% position:50% align:center
of Jesus’ life and how it’s depicted.

01:25:43.826 --> 01:25:46.245 line:90% position:50% align:center
But our film is so accurate.

01:25:46.245 --> 01:25:48.372 line:90% position:50% align:center
The research and effort that’s gone into it

01:25:48.372 --> 01:25:51.458 line:90% position:50% align:center
has made it so close to the Bible;

01:25:51.458 --> 01:25:53.210 line:90% position:50% align:center
it’s going to make such a difference.

01:25:53.210 --> 01:25:56.422 line:90% position:50% align:center
They’re going to see Jesus
and what he was truly like.

01:25:57.423 --> 01:25:58.632 line:10% position:50% align:center
It’s going to affect hearts,

01:25:58.632 --> 01:25:59.800 line:10% position:50% align:center
and it’s really going to help them

01:25:59.800 --> 01:26:01.552 line:10% position:50% align:center
to see Jehovah as well.

01:26:01.552 --> 01:26:02.636 line:10% position:50% align:center
As we’ve been working

01:26:02.636 --> 01:26:05.055 line:10% position:50% align:center
with <i>The Good News According to Jesus</i>  project,

01:26:05.055 --> 01:26:07.599 line:10% position:50% align:center
we’ve run into a few challenges, to say the least.

01:26:07.599 --> 01:26:10.185 line:10% position:50% align:center
Right from the start, we had fires,

01:26:10.185 --> 01:26:13.063 line:10% position:50% align:center
we had floods, and we had a pandemic.

01:26:13.063 --> 01:26:15.816 line:90% position:50% align:center
Because of a number of restrictions
that were taking place at the time,

01:26:15.816 --> 01:26:17.109 line:90% position:50% align:center
things were delayed.

01:26:17.109 --> 01:26:20.029 line:90% position:50% align:center
There even came a point
when it just completely stopped.

01:26:20.029 --> 01:26:21.739 line:90% position:50% align:center
But we did wonder how

01:26:21.739 --> 01:26:24.491 line:90% position:50% align:center
we were going to be able
to produce this video

01:26:24.491 --> 01:26:27.327 line:90% position:50% align:center
in the time frames
that we needed to do so.

01:26:30.330 --> 01:26:33.250 line:90% position:50% align:center
We had to pick and choose which scenes
that we had to shoot first

01:26:33.917 --> 01:26:37.171 line:90% position:50% align:center
because construction was trying
to keep up with our film schedule.

01:26:37.880 --> 01:26:41.675 line:90% position:50% align:center
So trying to manage
those two together was quite difficult.

01:26:42.384 --> 01:26:44.887 line:10% position:50% align:center
Some of the challenges also are depicting miracles.

01:26:44.887 --> 01:26:48.766 line:90% position:50% align:center
How are you going to depict
some of the various illnesses and diseases?

01:26:48.766 --> 01:26:51.935 line:90% position:50% align:center
How do we film scenes
like the miraculous catch of fish

01:26:51.935 --> 01:26:54.188 line:90% position:50% align:center
and Jesus walking on water

01:26:54.188 --> 01:26:56.190 line:90% position:50% align:center
in a realistic way?

01:26:56.190 --> 01:26:58.525 line:90% position:50% align:center
It’s a weighty responsibility,

01:26:58.525 --> 01:27:01.862 line:90% position:50% align:center
but there’s also the amazing joy
of being able to learn

01:27:01.862 --> 01:27:03.697 line:10% position:50% align:center
more about Jesus

01:27:03.697 --> 01:27:05.115 line:10% position:50% align:center
just through the process

01:27:05.115 --> 01:27:07.284 line:10% position:50% align:center
of trying to put it on film.

01:27:08.619 --> 01:27:10.537 line:10% position:50% align:center
The Bible accounts that we’re trying to depict

01:27:10.537 --> 01:27:12.331 line:10% position:50% align:center
involve a lot of animals.

01:27:12.331 --> 01:27:14.875 line:90% position:50% align:center
We know it was part of the culture
at the time.

01:27:14.875 --> 01:27:18.462 line:90% position:50% align:center
So we’re really trying to incorporate that
into this production.

01:27:18.462 --> 01:27:20.214 line:90% position:50% align:center
We’ve had donkeys,

01:27:20.214 --> 01:27:21.924 line:90% position:50% align:center
sheep,

01:27:21.924 --> 01:27:23.425 line:90% position:50% align:center
pigeons,

01:27:23.425 --> 01:27:25.677 line:90% position:50% align:center
and even camels here at the branch on set.

01:27:26.720 --> 01:27:28.430 line:10% position:50% align:center
They need to be trained to work with actors

01:27:28.430 --> 01:27:29.681 line:10% position:50% align:center
and trained to be ridden.

01:27:29.681 --> 01:27:32.434 line:90% position:50% align:center
They need to be familiarized with the sets.

01:27:33.143 --> 01:27:35.020 line:90% position:50% align:center
You actually start to see a bond established

01:27:35.020 --> 01:27:37.523 line:90% position:50% align:center
between the animals and the actors.

01:27:37.523 --> 01:27:39.399 line:90% position:50% align:center
Fortunately, many of our brothers and sisters

01:27:39.399 --> 01:27:41.693 line:90% position:50% align:center
that work in farmlands in rural Australia

01:27:41.693 --> 01:27:46.240 line:90% position:50% align:center
had many of these animals that they
were willing to make available for us.

01:27:46.240 --> 01:27:48.659 line:90% position:50% align:center
There’s a sister
in a nearby rural congregation

01:27:48.659 --> 01:27:51.245 line:90% position:50% align:center
who has volunteered to help raise

01:27:51.245 --> 01:27:54.665 line:90% position:50% align:center
the pigeons that we’re going to use
in the temple scenes and other areas.

01:27:54.665 --> 01:27:56.750 line:90% position:50% align:center
The sheep love to be around kids,

01:27:56.750 --> 01:27:59.419 line:90% position:50% align:center
and they love to be around the cast members.

01:27:59.419 --> 01:28:00.921 line:90% position:50% align:center
And it really does make a difference.

01:28:00.921 --> 01:28:03.507 line:90% position:50% align:center
All of those animals
essentially lend themselves

01:28:03.507 --> 01:28:05.676 line:90% position:50% align:center
to the realism of the sets that we’re in

01:28:05.676 --> 01:28:07.678 line:90% position:50% align:center
and help bring the Bible accounts to life.

01:28:10.139 --> 01:28:12.266 line:90% position:50% align:center
So one particular episode

01:28:12.266 --> 01:28:13.892 line:90% position:50% align:center
required the Judean wilderness.

01:28:14.643 --> 01:28:17.855 line:90% position:50% align:center
After reviewing a few options
here within the country of Australia,

01:28:17.855 --> 01:28:21.441 line:90% position:50% align:center
we saw that it wasn’t as feasible
as we would have liked for it to be.

01:28:21.441 --> 01:28:24.486 line:90% position:50% align:center
After presenting the information
to our brothers in oversight,

01:28:24.486 --> 01:28:27.447 line:90% position:50% align:center
we got a response
that we didn’t anticipate.

01:28:27.447 --> 01:28:30.284 line:90% position:50% align:center
They came back asking,
“What about Israel?”

01:28:31.201 --> 01:28:33.620 line:90% position:50% align:center
A small crew traveled to Israel

01:28:33.620 --> 01:28:36.165 line:90% position:50% align:center
and actually filmed
in the real Judean wilderness.

01:28:36.165 --> 01:28:39.084 line:90% position:50% align:center
The local branch office provided support,

01:28:39.084 --> 01:28:40.794 line:90% position:50% align:center
a number of scenes were filmed,

01:28:40.794 --> 01:28:42.796 line:90% position:50% align:center
and now when we’re reviewing the material,

01:28:42.796 --> 01:28:44.923 line:90% position:50% align:center
we see Jehovah blessing that arrangement.

01:28:47.009 --> 01:28:49.928 line:90% position:50% align:center
The back lot is a huge film set.

01:28:49.928 --> 01:28:52.055 line:90% position:50% align:center
It has five historical areas:

01:28:52.055 --> 01:28:54.725 line:90% position:50% align:center
We have the temple area and the temple slab;

01:28:54.725 --> 01:28:56.810 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jerusalem area;

01:28:56.810 --> 01:28:59.396 line:90% position:50% align:center
there’s Cana of Galilee;

01:28:59.396 --> 01:29:02.566 line:90% position:50% align:center
then there’s Capernaum,
including a little beach area;

01:29:02.566 --> 01:29:04.401 line:90% position:50% align:center
and Nazareth.

01:29:04.401 --> 01:29:07.487 line:90% position:50% align:center
The back lot has roads and mounds

01:29:07.487 --> 01:29:10.824 line:90% position:50% align:center
—just landscapes
so that we can have a variety of filming.

01:29:10.824 --> 01:29:13.869 line:90% position:50% align:center
It was designed in a way
where you can point the camera anywhere.

01:29:13.869 --> 01:29:17.956 line:90% position:50% align:center
So it just helps you immerse yourself
into the story and the life of Jesus.

01:29:17.956 --> 01:29:22.794 line:90% position:50% align:center
This is a world
that you’ve never seen before.

01:29:22.794 --> 01:29:24.922 line:90% position:50% align:center
What’s different
about those sets there in Australia

01:29:24.922 --> 01:29:27.883 line:90% position:50% align:center
than what we’re typically using here is

01:29:27.883 --> 01:29:29.635 line:90% position:50% align:center
they have to last a lot longer.

01:29:29.635 --> 01:29:33.305 line:90% position:50% align:center
To cover the entire span
of the Gospel accounts

01:29:33.305 --> 01:29:35.349 line:90% position:50% align:center
requires many, many years of recording.

01:29:37.851 --> 01:29:41.230 line:90% position:50% align:center
The brothers and sisters
have shown amazing skill,

01:29:41.230 --> 01:29:44.233 line:90% position:50% align:center
and they’ve worked
through some very challenging conditions.

01:29:44.233 --> 01:29:46.485 line:10% position:50% align:center
We’ve had heat, we’ve had rain,

01:29:46.485 --> 01:29:48.195 line:10% position:50% align:center
it’s been dusty out here,

01:29:48.195 --> 01:29:50.948 line:90% position:50% align:center
and it’s been muddy at times,
but they’ve worked through all of it.

01:29:52.115 --> 01:29:54.576 line:90% position:50% align:center
And whilst the end product
is this beautiful set,

01:29:54.576 --> 01:29:57.412 line:90% position:50% align:center
it’s going to bring
the ministry of Jesus Christ to life

01:29:57.412 --> 01:29:59.581 line:90% position:50% align:center
in an incredibly realistic way.

01:30:01.041 --> 01:30:02.376 line:90% position:50% align:center
While construction was going,

01:30:02.376 --> 01:30:06.296 line:90% position:50% align:center
a contractor came in to the back lot
to see the construction brothers.

01:30:06.296 --> 01:30:08.215 line:90% position:50% align:center
He spoke to one of the brothers

01:30:08.215 --> 01:30:11.176 line:90% position:50% align:center
and in tears asked what this was all about.

01:30:11.176 --> 01:30:13.679 line:90% position:50% align:center
And we explained
what we’re trying to achieve.

01:30:13.679 --> 01:30:17.683 line:90% position:50% align:center
And with tears, he said,
“I come from Israel,

01:30:17.683 --> 01:30:20.519 line:90% position:50% align:center
and this looks just like my home.”

01:30:20.519 --> 01:30:23.063 line:90% position:50% align:center
Seeing someone
who has no idea about this project

01:30:23.063 --> 01:30:25.274 line:90% position:50% align:center
come in
and say how accurate it was

01:30:25.274 --> 01:30:29.152 line:90% position:50% align:center
really shows me how Jehovah
is really looking after this project.

01:30:29.152 --> 01:30:32.281 line:90% position:50% align:center
It isn’t any one of us
that have made this a success;

01:30:32.281 --> 01:30:34.241 line:90% position:50% align:center
it’s Jehovah the whole way.

01:30:34.241 --> 01:30:35.993 line:90% position:50% align:center
As we study these Bible accounts

01:30:35.993 --> 01:30:39.121 line:90% position:50% align:center
and figure out ways
to bring them to life on the screen,

01:30:39.121 --> 01:30:42.291 line:90% position:50% align:center
it’s teaching us to get into the motivations
of who these people were.

01:30:42.958 --> 01:30:46.211 line:90% position:50% align:center
Our goal is to take them
from being just characters

01:30:46.211 --> 01:30:48.797 line:90% position:50% align:center
in black and white
on the printed page

01:30:48.797 --> 01:30:51.049 line:90% position:50% align:center
into real people
whom you’re going to know

01:30:51.049 --> 01:30:52.843 line:90% position:50% align:center
and love for the rest of your life.

01:31:02.894 --> 01:31:05.647 line:90% position:50% align:center
Roll camera!
Roll audio!

01:31:06.648 --> 01:31:08.692 line:90% position:50% align:center
And action!

01:31:30.339 --> 01:31:32.341 line:90% position:50% align:center
When we recount

01:31:32.341 --> 01:31:36.178 line:90% position:50% align:center
the tremendous amount
of work that is being done

01:31:36.178 --> 01:31:40.057 line:90% position:50% align:center
to visually portray, or depict,

01:31:40.057 --> 01:31:45.062 line:90% position:50% align:center
the Gospels of Jesus’ life and ministry,
we’re thrilled.

01:31:45.062 --> 01:31:47.647 line:90% position:50% align:center
We’re absolutely amazed.

01:31:47.647 --> 01:31:50.192 line:90% position:50% align:center
And all of this work and investment

01:31:50.192 --> 01:31:53.028 line:90% position:50% align:center
is not just for one convention drama.

01:31:53.028 --> 01:31:56.281 line:90% position:50% align:center
In fact, this production sets us up

01:31:56.281 --> 01:32:01.286 line:90% position:50% align:center
for convention dramas
for years to come in the future.

01:32:01.286 --> 01:32:06.166 line:90% position:50% align:center
And you’re going to truly enjoy them
as they’re rolled out.

01:32:06.166 --> 01:32:10.921 line:90% position:50% align:center
But now, when we think about
these dramas,

01:32:10.921 --> 01:32:12.589 line:90% position:50% align:center
these episodes,

01:32:12.589 --> 01:32:14.257 line:90% position:50% align:center
you probably want to know:

01:32:14.257 --> 01:32:17.677 line:90% position:50% align:center
‘When am I going to get to see
the first episode?

01:32:17.677 --> 01:32:19.179 line:90% position:50% align:center
When?’

01:32:19.179 --> 01:32:21.181 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, you’ll be happy to know

01:32:21.181 --> 01:32:24.309 line:90% position:50% align:center
that next year,

01:32:24.309 --> 01:32:26.353 line:90% position:50% align:center
2024,

01:32:26.353 --> 01:32:29.481 line:90% position:50% align:center
we’re going to have them portrayed

01:32:29.481 --> 01:32:33.402 line:90% position:50% align:center
into the convention program as two dramas

01:32:33.402 --> 01:32:36.655 line:90% position:50% align:center
—that is, Episode 1 will be two dramas

01:32:36.655 --> 01:32:40.075 line:90% position:50% align:center
at the 2024 convention,

01:32:40.075 --> 01:32:43.078 line:90% position:50% align:center
the regional and the special conventions.

01:32:43.078 --> 01:32:45.247 line:90% position:50% align:center
You’ll enjoy them, indeed.

01:32:57.592 --> 01:33:00.887 line:90% position:50% align:center
In fact, we’ve prepared a preview

01:33:00.887 --> 01:33:04.391 line:90% position:50% align:center
of those two convention dramas,

01:33:04.391 --> 01:33:07.727 line:90% position:50% align:center
and I think you’ll enjoy this short preview.

01:33:07.727 --> 01:33:11.106 line:90% position:50% align:center
I know it’s really early
to show you something

01:33:11.106 --> 01:33:14.151 line:90% position:50% align:center
for the 2024 convention,

01:33:14.151 --> 01:33:16.153 line:90% position:50% align:center
and I hope I don’t get into trouble

01:33:16.153 --> 01:33:19.781 line:90% position:50% align:center
with the Governing Body
for showing this prematurely.

01:33:21.741 --> 01:33:23.160 line:90% position:50% align:center
Just kidding!

01:33:24.411 --> 01:33:26.705 line:90% position:50% align:center
I hope you don’t think I’m that stupid.

01:33:34.296 --> 01:33:38.258 line:90% position:50% align:center
It is with the Governing Body’s
full blessing and approval

01:33:40.552 --> 01:33:42.596 line:90% position:50% align:center
that we show you this.

01:33:52.856 --> 01:33:54.858 line:90% position:50% align:center
So please enjoy

01:33:54.858 --> 01:33:59.029 line:90% position:50% align:center
this Governing-Body-approved teaser

01:33:59.029 --> 01:34:01.031 line:90% position:50% align:center
for these two dramas.

01:34:07.662 --> 01:34:09.498 line:90% position:50% align:center
Seeing that many have undertaken

01:34:09.498 --> 01:34:11.249 line:90% position:50% align:center
to compile an account of the facts,

01:34:14.711 --> 01:34:16.213 line:90% position:50% align:center
I resolved also,

01:34:17.797 --> 01:34:19.841 line:90% position:50% align:center
because I have traced all things

01:34:19.841 --> 01:34:22.511 line:90% position:50% align:center
from the start with accuracy.

01:34:26.598 --> 01:34:28.767 line:90% position:50% align:center
Do not be afraid, Mary.

01:34:30.310 --> 01:34:32.312 line:90% position:50% align:center
You will become pregnant

01:34:34.147 --> 01:34:35.857 line:90% position:50% align:center
and give birth to a son,

01:34:37.734 --> 01:34:42.364 line:90% position:50% align:center
and you are to name him Jesus.

01:34:44.824 --> 01:34:47.035 line:90% position:50% align:center
Let Jehovah be praised,

01:34:47.911 --> 01:34:49.287 line:90% position:50% align:center
the God of Israel,

01:34:50.747 --> 01:34:53.250 line:90% position:50% align:center
because he has turned his attention to his people

01:34:54.793 --> 01:34:56.836 line:90% position:50% align:center
and has brought them deliverance.

01:35:01.758 --> 01:35:03.051 line:90% position:50% align:center
For look!

01:35:03.051 --> 01:35:04.928 line:90% position:50% align:center
I am declaring to you good news.

01:35:06.972 --> 01:35:08.348 line:90% position:50% align:center
For today

01:35:08.932 --> 01:35:10.267 line:90% position:50% align:center
there was born to you

01:35:10.267 --> 01:35:13.186 line:90% position:50% align:center
in David’s city a savior,

01:35:13.979 --> 01:35:16.898 line:90% position:50% align:center
who is Christ the Lord.

01:35:21.236 --> 01:35:22.696 line:90% position:50% align:center
Look!

01:35:22.696 --> 01:35:24.614 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehovah’s slave girl!

01:35:27.242 --> 01:35:30.036 line:90% position:50% align:center
May it happen to me according to your declaration.

01:36:11.828 --> 01:36:13.538 line:90% position:50% align:center
The true light

01:36:13.538 --> 01:36:15.540 line:90% position:50% align:center
that gives light

01:36:15.540 --> 01:36:18.251 line:90% position:50% align:center
to every sort of man

01:36:18.251 --> 01:36:20.754 line:90% position:50% align:center
was about to come into the world.

01:36:49.908 --> 01:36:53.995 line:90% position:50% align:center
The dramas over the next several years

01:36:53.995 --> 01:36:56.373 line:90% position:50% align:center
will have this kind of realism

01:36:56.373 --> 01:37:01.378 line:90% position:50% align:center
and will truly bring
the Gospel account to life

01:37:01.378 --> 01:37:04.255 line:90% position:50% align:center
—<i>The Good News According to Jesus.</i>

01:37:04.255 --> 01:37:05.924 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, what you saw was just

01:37:05.924 --> 01:37:10.095 line:90% position:50% align:center
a two-and-a-half-minute teaser video,

01:37:10.095 --> 01:37:11.554 line:90% position:50% align:center
a little video.

01:37:11.554 --> 01:37:14.432 line:90% position:50% align:center
But as we mentioned, we’re going to—

01:37:14.432 --> 01:37:16.476 line:90% position:50% align:center
And that was just for Episode 1,

01:37:16.476 --> 01:37:19.354 line:90% position:50% align:center
but we are actively, speedily,

01:37:19.354 --> 01:37:24.025 line:90% position:50% align:center
fast-movingly preparing more episodes.

01:37:24.025 --> 01:37:27.153 line:90% position:50% align:center
In fact, you’ll be happy to know
that we’re working right now

01:37:27.153 --> 01:37:29.322 line:90% position:50% align:center
on the next four episodes

01:37:29.322 --> 01:37:31.658 line:90% position:50% align:center
after the two that

01:37:31.658 --> 01:37:35.412 line:90% position:50% align:center
—the one, really, teaser of the one—
you saw.

01:37:35.412 --> 01:37:37.872 line:90% position:50% align:center
Four more are being worked on,

01:37:37.872 --> 01:37:42.419 line:90% position:50% align:center
and Episode 3 is almost totally finished.

01:37:42.419 --> 01:37:45.130 line:90% position:50% align:center
We’ve almost got Episode 3 done.

01:37:45.130 --> 01:37:50.135 line:90% position:50% align:center
The Governing Body
has already been reviewing Episode 1

01:37:50.135 --> 01:37:53.096 line:90% position:50% align:center
and an early edition of Episode 2.

01:37:53.096 --> 01:37:57.058 line:90% position:50% align:center
And how powerful indeed they are!

01:37:57.058 --> 01:38:01.020 line:90% position:50% align:center
And I know personally I can say
that I’ve been inspired;

01:38:01.020 --> 01:38:02.564 line:90% position:50% align:center
I’ve been motivated

01:38:02.564 --> 01:38:05.859 line:90% position:50% align:center
and even brought
to the point of tears several times.

01:38:05.859 --> 01:38:10.196 line:90% position:50% align:center
And other Governing Body brothers
and helpers were affected similarly.

01:38:10.196 --> 01:38:12.949 line:90% position:50% align:center
The realism, the impact,

01:38:12.949 --> 01:38:17.203 line:90% position:50% align:center
and the power is absolutely amazing.

01:38:17.203 --> 01:38:21.124 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, we’re confident
that you appreciate receiving

01:38:21.124 --> 01:38:24.002 line:90% position:50% align:center
these two very important updates

01:38:24.002 --> 01:38:27.255 line:90% position:50% align:center
concerning significant fast-moving projects.

01:38:27.255 --> 01:38:31.593 line:90% position:50% align:center
And the Governing Body
wants to keep you fully informed.

01:38:31.593 --> 01:38:34.304 line:90% position:50% align:center
They really want you to be up-to-date

01:38:34.304 --> 01:38:37.140 line:90% position:50% align:center
because we need your prayers,
we need your support,

01:38:37.140 --> 01:38:40.310 line:90% position:50% align:center
and we want you to know what is happening.

01:38:40.310 --> 01:38:43.271 line:90% position:50% align:center
And we’re confident
that with Jehovah’s blessing,

01:38:43.271 --> 01:38:45.607 line:90% position:50% align:center
this is going to be something

01:38:45.607 --> 01:38:49.194 line:90% position:50% align:center
that’s going to benefit
the spiritual brotherhood

01:38:49.194 --> 01:38:52.489 line:90% position:50% align:center
in a tremendous and profound way.

01:38:52.489 --> 01:38:56.576 line:90% position:50% align:center
And we’re just so anxious
to be able to give you more of this,

01:38:56.576 --> 01:38:59.954 line:90% position:50% align:center
even though we gave you what we could now.

01:38:59.954 --> 01:39:02.248 line:90% position:50% align:center
But some might ask:

01:39:02.248 --> 01:39:06.211 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Why are we embarking

01:39:06.211 --> 01:39:08.463 line:90% position:50% align:center
“on two projects like this

01:39:08.463 --> 01:39:11.549 line:90% position:50% align:center
“when the new world is so close?

01:39:11.549 --> 01:39:13.593 line:90% position:50% align:center
“We might not even finish one of them.

01:39:13.593 --> 01:39:15.595 line:90% position:50% align:center
The end may come.”

01:39:15.595 --> 01:39:17.597 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, we just don’t know, do we?

01:39:17.597 --> 01:39:21.601 line:90% position:50% align:center
We don’t know exactly
when the end is going to come.

01:39:21.601 --> 01:39:24.229 line:90% position:50% align:center
Here’s an illustration:

01:39:24.229 --> 01:39:27.482 line:90% position:50% align:center
How many carefully selected smooth stones

01:39:27.482 --> 01:39:30.360 line:90% position:50% align:center
did David take out
when he went to fight Goliath?

01:39:31.277 --> 01:39:32.779 line:90% position:50% align:center
He took five, didn’t he?

01:39:32.779 --> 01:39:34.614 line:90% position:50% align:center
How many did he need?

01:39:34.614 --> 01:39:35.824 line:90% position:50% align:center
One.

01:39:35.824 --> 01:39:37.450 line:90% position:50% align:center
He just didn’t know, did he?

01:39:37.450 --> 01:39:40.620 line:90% position:50% align:center
So he was prepared for whatever it took.

01:39:40.620 --> 01:39:42.914 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, in the same way,
we don’t know when the end is going to come.

01:39:42.914 --> 01:39:45.792 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, here’s another thought,
food for thought:

01:39:45.792 --> 01:39:49.337 line:90% position:50% align:center
Could not these projects, if needed,

01:39:49.337 --> 01:39:52.507 line:90% position:50% align:center
be finished after the great tribulation

01:39:52.507 --> 01:39:55.301 line:90% position:50% align:center
and then be used powerfully in the new world?

01:39:55.301 --> 01:39:59.722 line:90% position:50% align:center
And thinking of <i>The Good News</i>
<i>According to Jesus </i> episodes,

01:39:59.722 --> 01:40:02.225 line:90% position:50% align:center
would they not be wonderful tools

01:40:02.225 --> 01:40:05.895 line:90% position:50% align:center
to teach resurrected ones about God’s Son?

01:40:05.895 --> 01:40:07.730 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, only Jehovah knows.

01:40:07.730 --> 01:40:09.732 line:90% position:50% align:center
Time will tell.

01:40:09.732 --> 01:40:13.152 line:90% position:50% align:center
But what did <i>The Watchtower</i>  say
some years ago

01:40:13.152 --> 01:40:17.031 line:90% position:50% align:center
about the activity

01:40:17.031 --> 01:40:20.285 line:90% position:50% align:center
of Jehovah’s people
right when the end would come?

01:40:20.285 --> 01:40:22.620 line:90% position:50% align:center
Here’s what it said;
let me read you this quote.

01:40:22.620 --> 01:40:25.331 line:90% position:50% align:center
It said:

01:40:25.331 --> 01:40:30.044 line:90% position:50% align:center
“The arrival of the Lord Jesus
to execute judgment

01:40:30.044 --> 01:40:34.424 line:90% position:50% align:center
“will come as a complete surprise

01:40:34.424 --> 01:40:37.302 line:90% position:50% align:center
“—even to Jehovah’s people,

01:40:37.302 --> 01:40:42.307 line:90% position:50% align:center
for it will no doubt find them
at their busiest time of activity!”

01:40:42.891 --> 01:40:45.101 line:90% position:50% align:center
So we’re going to be surprised.

01:40:45.101 --> 01:40:47.145 line:90% position:50% align:center
We’re going to be very busy
when the end comes.

01:40:47.145 --> 01:40:49.188 line:90% position:50% align:center
And we say— If the end comes

01:40:49.188 --> 01:40:51.900 line:90% position:50% align:center
before we finish
either one of these projects,

01:40:51.900 --> 01:40:53.902 line:90% position:50% align:center
then we say: “Hallelujah!

01:40:54.861 --> 01:40:56.863 line:90% position:50% align:center
Praise Jah!”

01:40:56.863 --> 01:41:00.366 line:90% position:50% align:center
But we’re going to be busy
right up until the end

01:41:00.366 --> 01:41:02.911 line:90% position:50% align:center
—Jehovah with his help and his support.

01:41:02.911 --> 01:41:04.746 line:90% position:50% align:center
And you think of the scripture

01:41:04.746 --> 01:41:08.249 line:90% position:50% align:center
at 2 Kings 13:18.

01:41:08.249 --> 01:41:11.085 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehovah was not at all pleased

01:41:11.085 --> 01:41:13.338 line:90% position:50% align:center
with King Jehoash.

01:41:13.338 --> 01:41:15.340 line:90% position:50% align:center
Remember, he took the arrows,

01:41:15.340 --> 01:41:19.260 line:90% position:50% align:center
he struck the ground three times,
and then he stopped.

01:41:19.260 --> 01:41:20.678 line:90% position:50% align:center
Why?

01:41:20.678 --> 01:41:22.680 line:90% position:50% align:center
Because Jehovah does not like

01:41:22.680 --> 01:41:26.059 line:90% position:50% align:center
—and he doesn’t bless—
a lack of zeal and enthusiasm.

01:41:26.059 --> 01:41:29.395 line:90% position:50% align:center
So we want to make sure
we’re zealously working

01:41:29.395 --> 01:41:32.523 line:90% position:50% align:center
right up until the end comes.

01:41:32.523 --> 01:41:34.525 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, in conclusion,

01:41:34.525 --> 01:41:37.153 line:90% position:50% align:center
we say with your continued support

01:41:37.153 --> 01:41:40.198 line:90% position:50% align:center
and prayers in our behalf,

01:41:40.198 --> 01:41:43.159 line:90% position:50% align:center
fast-moving and amazing things are happening

01:41:43.159 --> 01:41:46.537 line:90% position:50% align:center
in the earthly part
of Jehovah’s organization.

01:41:46.537 --> 01:41:49.374 line:90% position:50% align:center
And we give all thanks to Jehovah,

01:41:49.374 --> 01:41:53.711 line:90% position:50% align:center
that great celestial chariot Rider.

01:41:53.711 --> 01:41:55.755 line:90% position:50% align:center
We give thanks to him,

01:41:55.755 --> 01:41:59.968 line:90% position:50% align:center
and we give thanks
to the heavenly part of his organization.

01:41:59.968 --> 01:42:02.595 line:90% position:50% align:center
How we appreciate

01:42:02.595 --> 01:42:05.682 line:90% position:50% align:center
the direction we are receiving

01:42:05.682 --> 01:42:08.267 line:90% position:50% align:center
by means of holy spirit!

01:42:14.023 --> 01:42:16.401 line:90% position:50% align:center
You keep clapping,
and I’ll just keep smiling.

01:42:17.860 --> 01:42:22.573 line:90% position:50% align:center
That’s wonderful.
That was a very rich series of talks.

01:42:22.573 --> 01:42:24.951 line:90% position:50% align:center
And we thank you, dear brothers, very much.

01:42:24.951 --> 01:42:27.161 line:90% position:50% align:center
And above all, we thank Jehovah

01:42:27.161 --> 01:42:31.416 line:90% position:50% align:center
for how he is guiding us
through all of these wonderful things.

01:42:31.416 --> 01:42:35.795 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, those of you listening
no doubt picked up on adjustments being made

01:42:35.795 --> 01:42:40.800 line:90% position:50% align:center
by “the faithful and discreet slave,”
based on Scriptural principles

01:42:40.800 --> 01:42:43.970 line:90% position:50% align:center
in Jehovah’s precious Word, the Bible.

01:42:45.596 --> 01:42:48.349 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, at the beginning of the program,
we mentioned

01:42:48.349 --> 01:42:52.645 line:90% position:50% align:center
there was
a landmark annual meeting ten years ago.

01:42:52.645 --> 01:42:54.772 line:90% position:50% align:center
And now with what we’ve learned today

01:42:54.772 --> 01:42:58.484 line:90% position:50% align:center
about Jehovah’s mercy and his judgment

01:42:58.484 --> 01:43:02.822 line:90% position:50% align:center
as well as our personal responsibility
before him,

01:43:02.822 --> 01:43:04.991 line:90% position:50% align:center
we see the power of God’s Word

01:43:04.991 --> 01:43:09.120 line:90% position:50% align:center
and its principles at work, don’t we?

01:43:09.120 --> 01:43:12.165 line:90% position:50% align:center
So, then, this program too is truly landmark.

01:43:12.165 --> 01:43:14.333 line:90% position:50% align:center
And as one of the branches wrote in,

01:43:14.333 --> 01:43:18.504 line:90% position:50% align:center
it is indeed one
that we will always remember.

01:43:18.504 --> 01:43:21.549 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, it’s fitting,
as we approach the great tribulation,

01:43:21.549 --> 01:43:24.260 line:90% position:50% align:center
that we now have received
a better understanding of these things,

01:43:24.260 --> 01:43:25.553 line:90% position:50% align:center
don’t you agree?

01:43:25.553 --> 01:43:26.888 line:90% position:50% align:center
It’s very good.

01:43:26.888 --> 01:43:29.599 line:90% position:50% align:center
As Proverbs 3:5 urges us,

01:43:29.599 --> 01:43:34.020 line:90% position:50% align:center
keep “[trusting] in Jehovah
with all your heart . . .

01:43:34.020 --> 01:43:37.940 line:90% position:50% align:center
do not rely on your own understanding,”

01:43:37.940 --> 01:43:41.235 line:90% position:50% align:center
and as we do this,
our heavenly Father promises

01:43:41.235 --> 01:43:43.738 line:90% position:50% align:center
to “make [our] paths straight.”

01:43:43.738 --> 01:43:45.406 line:90% position:50% align:center
And he is certainly doing that.

01:43:45.406 --> 01:43:48.117 line:90% position:50% align:center
And we love him so much for doing that.

01:43:48.117 --> 01:43:51.704 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehovah gets the praise for everything

01:43:51.704 --> 01:43:54.207 line:90% position:50% align:center
that has come out in this annual meeting,

01:43:54.207 --> 01:43:56.876 line:90% position:50% align:center
and we give much credit

01:43:56.876 --> 01:43:59.504 line:90% position:50% align:center
to his dear Son, our King, Christ Jesus.

01:43:59.504 --> 01:44:01.839 line:90% position:50% align:center
What a delight to serve

01:44:01.839 --> 01:44:04.842 line:90% position:50% align:center
in this way under their guidance!

01:44:05.259 --> 01:44:08.805 line:90% position:50% align:center
We are sure you enjoyed
Part 2 of the annual meeting.

01:44:08.805 --> 01:44:12.975 line:90% position:50% align:center
It’s always a joy to share
this momentous occasion with all of you.

01:44:13.810 --> 01:44:15.645 line:90% position:50% align:center
Our postcard for this month

01:44:15.645 --> 01:44:19.232 line:90% position:50% align:center
is from the smallest country
in the Western Hemisphere

01:44:19.232 --> 01:44:22.693 line:90% position:50% align:center
—the Federation of Saint Kitts and Nevis.

01:44:22.693 --> 01:44:25.613 line:90% position:50% align:center
St. Kitts and Nevis
lie in the Leeward Islands

01:44:25.613 --> 01:44:28.366 line:90% position:50% align:center
in the eastern Caribbean Sea.

01:44:28.366 --> 01:44:30.368 line:90% position:50% align:center
The islands are known for their beaches,

01:44:30.368 --> 01:44:32.787 line:90% position:50% align:center
reefs, and tropical weather.

01:44:34.330 --> 01:44:38.543 line:90% position:50% align:center
A channel called The Narrows
separates the two volcanic isles.

01:44:38.543 --> 01:44:41.796 line:90% position:50% align:center
Mount Liamuiga, at the center of St. Kitts,

01:44:41.796 --> 01:44:44.423 line:90% position:50% align:center
is one of the highest volcanoes
in the Caribbean.

01:44:44.423 --> 01:44:47.009 line:90% position:50% align:center
Liamuiga is the name given to the island

01:44:47.009 --> 01:44:49.095 line:90% position:50% align:center
by the Kalinago Indians.

01:44:49.095 --> 01:44:52.181 line:90% position:50% align:center
It can be translated as “fertile land,”

01:44:52.181 --> 01:44:55.393 line:90% position:50% align:center
a fitting description
for how the volcanic soil

01:44:55.393 --> 01:44:57.395 line:90% position:50% align:center
yields abundant crops.

01:44:57.979 --> 01:45:02.650 line:90% position:50% align:center
But St. Kitts and Nevis have proven
to be spiritually fruitful as well.

01:45:02.650 --> 01:45:06.571 line:90% position:50% align:center
The good news spread
to St. Kitts and Nevis in the 1930’s.

01:45:07.446 --> 01:45:09.657 line:90% position:50% align:center
During World War II, however,

01:45:09.657 --> 01:45:12.451 line:90% position:50% align:center
the importation of our literature was banned.

01:45:12.451 --> 01:45:14.453 line:90% position:50% align:center
Cartons containing the books

01:45:14.453 --> 01:45:16.664 line:90% position:50% align:center
<i>Children </i> and <i>The New World </i>

01:45:16.664 --> 01:45:18.875 line:90% position:50% align:center
as well as the Watch Tower edition

01:45:18.875 --> 01:45:21.085 line:90% position:50% align:center
of the <i>American Standard Version </i> Bible

01:45:21.085 --> 01:45:25.047 line:90% position:50% align:center
were confiscated
to be burned at a sugar factory.

01:45:25.047 --> 01:45:28.009 line:90% position:50% align:center
Two courageous brothers
worked at the factory

01:45:28.009 --> 01:45:32.138 line:90% position:50% align:center
and saved enough books and Bibles
for the congregation.

01:45:32.138 --> 01:45:34.140 line:90% position:50% align:center
When going door to door,

01:45:34.140 --> 01:45:36.726 line:90% position:50% align:center
our brothers generally don’t knock.

01:45:36.726 --> 01:45:40.021 line:90% position:50% align:center
Instead, they call out “Inside!”

01:45:40.021 --> 01:45:43.733 line:90% position:50% align:center
to make it clear that they are looking
for someone inside the house,

01:45:43.733 --> 01:45:47.570 line:90% position:50% align:center
not calling for someone on the street
or in a neighboring yard.

01:45:47.570 --> 01:45:49.822 line:90% position:50% align:center
The people of St. Kitts and Nevis

01:45:49.822 --> 01:45:54.243 line:90% position:50% align:center
spend much time outside the home,
working or visiting with family and friends,

01:45:55.411 --> 01:45:57.830 line:90% position:50% align:center
so it can be difficult to find them at home.

01:45:57.830 --> 01:46:01.792 line:90% position:50% align:center
Publishers look for opportunities to witness
wherever they are.

01:46:02.585 --> 01:46:06.297 line:90% position:50% align:center
Tourism makes up a large part of the economy,

01:46:06.297 --> 01:46:10.301 line:90% position:50% align:center
with hundreds of thousands
—that is, many times the local population—

01:46:10.301 --> 01:46:12.303 line:90% position:50% align:center
visiting each year by cruise ship.

01:46:12.303 --> 01:46:16.057 line:90% position:50% align:center
Many of these tourists
will pass one of our literature carts.

01:46:17.016 --> 01:46:18.434 line:90% position:50% align:center
Since it’s expensive

01:46:18.434 --> 01:46:22.146 line:90% position:50% align:center
to travel to another island
for assemblies and conventions,

01:46:22.146 --> 01:46:24.440 line:90% position:50% align:center
St. Kitts has what is called

01:46:24.440 --> 01:46:26.651 line:90% position:50% align:center
an expandable Kingdom Hall.

01:46:26.651 --> 01:46:31.072 line:90% position:50% align:center
For most of the year, it functions as
a normal Kingdom Hall for two congregations.

01:46:31.072 --> 01:46:34.617 line:90% position:50% align:center
But for our three
larger theocratic events each year,

01:46:34.617 --> 01:46:37.245 line:90% position:50% align:center
added chairs increase the capacity.

01:46:37.245 --> 01:46:41.707 line:90% position:50% align:center
Baptismal candidates travel to the nearby
Timothy Bay for water immersion.

01:46:42.333 --> 01:46:43.960 line:90% position:50% align:center
The expandable Kingdom Hall

01:46:43.960 --> 01:46:47.338 line:90% position:50% align:center
also provides needed space
for the Memorial attendees,

01:46:47.338 --> 01:46:50.633 line:90% position:50% align:center
often three times
the number of the publishers!

01:46:50.633 --> 01:46:53.219 line:90% position:50% align:center
The 326 publishers

01:46:53.219 --> 01:46:56.222 line:90% position:50% align:center
from all four congregations
in St. Kitts and Nevis

01:46:56.222 --> 01:46:58.683 line:90% position:50% align:center
send their warm love and greetings

01:46:58.683 --> 01:47:00.685 line:90% position:50% align:center
to the entire brotherhood!

01:47:01.185 --> 01:47:04.105 line:90% position:50% align:center
From the World Headquarters
of Jehovah’s Witnesses,

01:47:04.105 --> 01:47:06.649 line:90% position:50% align:center
this is JW Broadcasting.

